  91        def is_in_responsive_mode(self) -> bool:
  92            """
  93            Determine if the Power Chart is in responsive mode.
  94
  95            :returns: True, if the Power Chart is currently displaying in a responsive layout - False otherwise.
  96            """
  97            try:
  98                return "mobile" in self.find().get_attribute(name="class")
  99            except TimeoutException as toe:
 100                raise TimeoutException(msg="Unable to locate the Power Chart as defined by its locator") from toe

 102    class _PowerChartGraph(ComponentPiece):
 103        _LINE_CHART_CONTAINER_LOCATOR = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, "div.main-chart-container")
 104        _GRAPHED_LINE_LOCATOR = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, f"g.ia_lineChart > g > g")

 106        _GRAPH_CONTAINER_LOCATOR = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, "g.chart-row")
 107        _LABEL_LOCATOR = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, "text.ia_powerChartComponent__timeAxis__values")
 108        _Y_AXIS_GRID_LOCATOR = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, "line.ia_powerChartComponent__yAxis__grid")
 109        _X_AXIS_GRID_LOCATOR = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, "line.ia_powerChartComponent__timeAxis__grid")
 110        _X_AXIS_LOCATOR = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, "line.ia_powerChartComponent__timeAxis__axis")
 111        _Y_AXIS_LABEL_LOCATOR = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, "text.ia_powerChartComponent__yAxis__label")

 114        def __init__(
 115                self,
 116                parent_locator_list: List[Tuple[By, str]],
 117                driver: WebDriver,
 118                description: Optional[str] = None,
 119                poll_freq: float = 0.5):
 120            super().__init__(
 121                parent_locator_list=parent_locator_list,
 122                driver=driver,
 123                locator=self._LINE_CHART_CONTAINER_LOCATOR,
 124                description=description,
 125                poll_freq=poll_freq)
 126            self._row_container = ComponentPiece(
 127                locator=self._GRAPH_CONTAINER_LOCATOR,
 128                driver=driver,
 129                parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
 130                description="The container of all graphed lines in the chart.",
 131                poll_freq=poll_freq)
 132            self._graphed_line = ComponentPiece(
 133                locator=self._GRAPHED_LINE_LOCATOR,
 134                driver=driver,
 135                parent_locator_list=self._row_container.locator_list,
 136                description="The actual graphed line.",
 137                poll_freq=poll_freq)
 138            self._line_paths = ComponentPiece(
 139                parent_locator_list=self._graphed_line.locator_list,
 140                locator=self._LINE_PATH_LOCATOR,
 141                driver=driver,
 142                description="The <path> element within the line which describes the drawn path of the line.",
 143                poll_freq=poll_freq)
 144            self._time_axis_labels = ComponentPiece(
 145                locator=self._LABEL_LOCATOR,
 146                driver=driver,
 147                parent_locator_list=parent_locator_list,
 148                description="The labels of the time axis, usually found along the bottom of the graphed lines.",
 149                poll_freq=poll_freq)
 150            self._y_axis_grid_line = ComponentPiece(
 151                locator=self._Y_AXIS_GRID_LOCATOR,
 152                driver=driver,
 153                parent_locator_list=parent_locator_list,
 154                poll_freq=poll_freq)
 155            self._x_axis_grid_line = ComponentPiece(
 156                locator=self._X_AXIS_GRID_LOCATOR,
 157                driver=driver,
 158                parent_locator_list=parent_locator_list,
 159                poll_freq=poll_freq)
 160            self._x_axis = ComponentPiece(
 161                locator=self._X_AXIS_LOCATOR,
 162                driver=driver,
 163                parent_locator_list=parent_locator_list,
 164                description="The line which defines the bottom of the graphed area.",
 165                poll_freq=poll_freq)
 166            self._y_axis_label = ComponentPiece(
 167                locator=self._Y_AXIS_LABEL_LOCATOR,
 168                driver=driver,
 169                parent_locator_list=parent_locator_list,
 170                description="The labels of the Y axis, which can be found to either the left or right of the graphed "
 171                            "lines.",
 172                poll_freq=poll_freq)
 173            self._y_axis = ComponentPiece(
 174                locator=self._Y_AXIS_LOCATOR,
 175                driver=driver,
 176                parent_locator_list=parent_locator_list,
 177                description="The line which defines either the left or right border of the graph.",
 178                poll_freq=poll_freq)

 180        def get_count_of_graphed_pens(self) -> int:
 181            """
 182            Obtain a count of pens which are displayed in the chart.
 183
 184            :returns: A count of pens currently rendered in the chart.
 185            """
 186            try:
 187                # each graphed pen has 2 <path> elements
 188                return int(len(self._line_paths.find_all(wait_timeout=1)) / 2)
 189            except TimeoutException:
 190                return 0
 191
 192        def get_displayed_time_axis_labels(self) -> List[str]:
 193            """
 194            Obtain the labels displayed on the X (time) axis.
 195
 196            :returns: A list which contains all currently displayed labels from the X (time) axis.
 197
 198            :raises TimeoutException: If no labels are displayed on the X (time) axis.
 199            """
 200            try:
 201                return [_.text for _ in self._time_axis_labels.find_all()]
 202            except TimeoutException as toe:
 203                raise TimeoutException(msg="No labels displayed for the Power Chart") from toe
 204
 205        def get_drawn_path(self, pen_checkbox_color_as_string: str) -> str:
 206            """
 207            Obtain the drawn path of a graphed pen. Useful for determining when a graphed pen has updated.
 208
 209            :param pen_checkbox_color_as_string: The color used to graph the pen for which you would like the drawn
 210                path.
 211
 212            :returns: A string which represents the actual graphed line of a pen.
 213
 214            :raises IndexError: If no graphed pen has the supplied color.
 215            :raises TimeoutException: If no pens are graphed.
 216            """
 217            try:
 218                return list(
 219                    filter(
 220                        lambda e: e.value_of_css_property(CSS.STROKE.value) == pen_checkbox_color_as_string,
 221                        self._line_paths.find_all()))[0].get_attribute("d")
 222            except TimeoutException as toe:
 223                raise TimeoutException(msg="No pens are currently graphed.") from toe
 224            except IndexError as ie:
 225                raise IndexError(f"No pen graphed with a color of '{pen_checkbox_color_as_string}'.") from ie
 226
 227        def get_x_axis_html_class(self) -> str:
 228            """
 229            Obtain the HTML class of the X axis.
 230
 231            :returns: The class of the X axis as it exists in the DOM.
 232
 233            :raises TimeoutException: If no X axis is present.
 234            """
 235            try:
 236                return self._x_axis.find().get_attribute(name="class")
 237            except TimeoutException as toe:
 238                raise TimeoutException(msg="No X axis present.") from toe
 239
 240        def get_x_axis_css_property_value(self, property_name: Union[CSSPropertyValue, str]) -> str:
 241            """
 242            Obtain the value of a CSS property from the X axis.
 243
 244            :param property_name: The name of the CSS property you would like the value of.
 245
 246            :returns: The value of the requested CSS property.
 247
 248            :raises TimeoutException: If no labels are present on the X (time) axis.
 249            """
 250            try:
 251                return self._time_axis_labels.get_css_property(property_name=property_name)
 252            except TimeoutException as toe:
 253                raise TimeoutException(msg="No labels are present for the X (time) axis.") from toe

 298        def click_and_drag_chart(self, x_offset: int = 0, y_offset: int = 0) -> None:
 299            """
 300            Blindly click within the Power Chart and then drag some number of pixels before releasing the click event.
 301
 302            :param x_offset: The number of pixels to the right of the upper left corner to click.
 303            :param y_offset: The number of pixels down from the upper left corner to click.
 304            """
 305            ActionChains(driver=self.driver) \
 306                .click_and_hold(on_element=self.find()) \
 307                .move_by_offset(xoffset=x_offset, yoffset=y_offset) \
 308                .release() \
 309                .perform()
 310            self.wait_on_binding(time_to_wait=1)
 311
 312        def get_count_of_x_axis_grid_lines(self, _already_attempted=False) -> int:
 313            """
 314            Obtain a count of lines displayed on the X axis.
 315
 316            :param _already_attempted: Used internally to re-try in the event the Power Chart updates.
 317
 318            :returns: A count of vertical lines currently displayed on the X axis of the Power Chart.
 319            """
 320            try:
 321                return len(self._x_axis_grid_line.find_all())
 322            except TimeoutException:
 323                return 0
 324            except StaleElementReferenceException as sere:
 325                if not _already_attempted:
 326                    return self.get_count_of_x_axis_grid_lines(
 327                        _already_attempted=True)
 328                else:
 329                    raise sere
 330
 331        def get_count_of_y_axis_grid_lines(self, _already_attempted=False) -> int:
 332            """
 333            Obtain a count of lines displayed on the Y axis.
 334
 335            :param _already_attempted: Used internally to re-try in the event the Power Chart updates.
 336
 337            :returns: A count of horizontal lines currently displayed on the Y axis of the Power Chart.
 338            """
 339            try:
 340                return len(self._y_axis_grid_line.find_all())
 341            except TimeoutException:
 342                return 0
 343            except StaleElementReferenceException as sere:
 344                if not _already_attempted:
 345                    return self.get_count_of_y_axis_grid_lines(
 346                        _already_attempted=True)
 347                else:
 348                    raise sere
 349
 350        def get_css_property_from_x_axis_grid(self, property_name: Union[CSSPropertyValue, str]) -> str:
 351            """
 352            Obtain the value of a CSS property from the grid of the X axis.
 353
 354            :param property_name: The name of the property you want to value of.
 355
 356            :returns: The value of the requested CSS property from the X axis grid.
 357
 358            :raises TimeoutException: If no X axis grid is present.
 359            """
 360            try:
 361                return self._x_axis_grid_line.get_css_property(property_name=property_name)
 362            except StaleElementReferenceException:
 363                return self.get_css_property_from_x_axis_grid(property_name=property_name)
 364            except TimeoutException as toe:
 365                raise TimeoutException(
 366                    msg="No grid line was found for the X axis.") from toe
 367
 368        def get_css_property_from_y_axis_grid(self, property_name: Union[CSSPropertyValue, str]) -> str:
 369            """
 370            Obtain the value of a CSS property from the grid of the Y axis.
 371
 372            :param property_name: The name of the property you want to value of.
 373
 374            :returns: The value of the requested CSS property from the Y axis grid.
 375
 376            :raises TimeoutException: If no Y axis grid is present.
 377            """
 378            try:
 379                return self._y_axis_grid_line.get_css_property(property_name=property_name)
 380            except StaleElementReferenceException:
 381                return self.get_css_property_from_y_axis_grid(
 382                    property_name=property_name)
 383            except TimeoutException as toe:
 384                raise TimeoutException(
 385                    msg="No grid line was found for the Y axis.") from toe

 387        def line_is_displayed_by_color(self, pen_checkbox_color_as_str: str) -> bool:
 388            """
 389            Determine if a line is graphed.
 390
 391            :param pen_checkbox_color_as_str: The color to look for in the graph. This value MUST be supplied in the
 392                same form as the browser in use would return a color value. It is recommended to avoid supplying
 393                hard-coded colors and instead supply values retrieved from the browser.
 394
 395            :returns: True, if any graphed line uses the supplied color - False otherwise.
 396            """
 397            try:
 398                return len(
 399                    list(
 400                        filter(
 401                            lambda e: e.value_of_css_property(CSS.STROKE.value) == pen_checkbox_color_as_str,
 402                            self._line_paths.find_all()))) == 1
 403            except TimeoutException:
 404                return False
 405
 406        def set_range_brush_basic(self) -> None:
 407            """
 408            Applies the range brush to the graph via a short drag event.
 409            """
 410            self.click_and_drag_chart(x_offset=100, y_offset=0)

 414        The header of the Power Chart, where the Option Bar Buttons live, as well as the range selector.

 463        def apply_changes(self) -> None:
 464            """
 465            Click the Apply button in the range selector.
 466
 467            :raises TimeoutException: If the range selector is not present, or if the Apply button is not present.
 468            """
 469            self._date_range_selector.apply_changes()

 471        def button_is_active(self, option_bar_button: OptionBarButton) -> bool:
 472            """
 473            Determine if an Option Bar button is active (selected/in-use).
 474
 475            :param option_bar_button: The Option Bar button to check the status of.
 476
 477            :returns: True, if the supplied Option Bar button is active - False otherwise.
 478            """
 479            try:
 480                if option_bar_button == OptionBarButton.FULL_SCREEN:
 481                    # special handling for fullscreen button
 482                    return self._FULLSCREEN_BUTTON_ACTIVE_PATH \
 483                        == self._fullscreen_button_path.find().get_attribute(
 484                            name="d")
 485                else:
 486                    return self._BUTTON_ACTIVE_CLASS in self._get_option_bar_button(
 487                        option_bar_button=option_bar_button).find().get_attribute("class")
 488            except TimeoutException as toe:
 489                raise TimeoutException(
 490                    msg=f"No {option_bar_button.value} button found among the Option Bar buttons.") from toe
 491
 492        def button_is_displayed(self, option_bar_button: OptionBarButton) -> bool:
 493            """
 494            Determine if an Option Bar button is displayed.
 495
 496            :param option_bar_button: The Option Bar button we will check.
 497
 498            :returns: True, if the supplied Option Bar button is displayed - False otherwise.
 499            """
 500            try:
 501                return self._get_option_bar_button(option_bar_button=option_bar_button).find().is_displayed()
 502            except TimeoutException:
 503                return False
 504
 505        def click_option_bar_button(self, option_bar_button: OptionBarButton) -> None:
 506            """
 507            Click a button located within the Option Bar area.
 508
 509            :param option_bar_button: The Option Bar button to click.
 510
 511            :raises TimeoutException: if the supplied button is not present.
 512            """
 513            try:
 514                self._get_option_bar_button(option_bar_button=option_bar_button).click()
 515            except TimeoutException as toe:
 516                raise TimeoutException(
 517                    msg=f"No {option_bar_button.value} button found among the Option Bar buttons.") from toe
 518
 519        def click_tag_browser_button(self) -> None:
 520            """
 521            Click the button which expands or collapses the Tag Browser panel.
 522
 523            :raises TimeoutException: If the Tag Browse button is not present.
 524            """
 525            try:
 526                self._tag_browser_button.click()
 527            except TimeoutException as toe:
 528                raise TimeoutException(msg="The Tag browse button is not present.") from toe
 529
 530        def date_range_selector_expansion_icon_is_displayed(self) -> bool:
 531            """
 532            Determine if the Date Range selector is displayed.
 533
 534            :returns: True, if the date range selector is currently displayed - False otherwise.
 535            """
 536            return self._date_range_selector.date_range_selector_toggle_icon_is_present()
 537
 538        def get_historical_range(self) -> HistoricalRange:
 539            """
 540            Obtain the applied historical range as an object. Expands the range selector if not already open, and then
 541            closes the range selector if it was not open to start with.
 542
 543            :returns: The applied historical range as a HistoricalRange object.
 544            """
 545            return self._date_range_selector.get_historical_range()
 546
 547        def get_date_range_message(self) -> str:
 548            """
 549            Obtain the range message associated with the Date Range Selector. This value describes the applied range.
 550            Example: 'Last 8 hours', or a breakdown of the date/times used for the Historical range.
 551
 552            :returns: The range message associated with the Date Range Selector, if available.
 553
 554            :raises TimeoutException: If the Power Chart has made the Date Range Selector invisible.
 555            """
 556            return self._date_range_selector.get_range_message()
 557
 558        def get_title_html_class(self) -> str:
 559            """
 560            Obtain the html class attribute for the title of the header.
 561
 562            :returns: The HTML class attribute for the title of the header of the Power Chart.
 563
 564            :raises TimeoutException: If the title is not present.
 565            """
 566            try:
 567                return self._title.find().get_attribute(name="class")
 568            except TimeoutException as toe:
 569                raise TimeoutException(msg="No title is present in the header of the Power Chart.") from toe
 570
 571        def get_css_property_value_from_title(self, property_name: Union[CSSPropertyValue, str]) -> str:
 572            """
 573            Obtain the value of a CSS property from the title of the header.
 574
 575            :param property_name: The name of the property you want to value of.
 576
 577            :returns: The value of the supplied CSS property of the title of the header of the Power Chart.
 578
 579            :raises TimeoutException: If the title is not present.
 580            """
 581            try:
 582                return self._title.get_css_property(property_name=property_name)
 583            except TimeoutException as toe:
 584                raise TimeoutException(msg="No title is present in the header of the Power Chart.") from toe
 585
 586        def hover_over_option_bar_button(self, option_bar_button: OptionBarButton) -> None:
 587            """
 588            Hover over a button of the Option Bar.
 589
 590            :param option_bar_button: The Option Bar button to hover over.
 591
 592            :raises TimeoutException: If the supplied Option Bar button is not present.
 593            """
 594            try:
 595                IASelenium(driver=self.driver).hover_over_web_element(
 596                    web_element=self._get_option_bar_button(option_bar_button=option_bar_button).find())
 597            except TimeoutException as toe:
 598                raise TimeoutException(msg=f"No {option_bar_button.value} Option Bar button found.") from toe
 599
 600        def is_in_responsive_mode(self) -> bool:
 601            """
 602            Determine if the Power Chart is displaying in responsive mode.
 603
 604            :returns: True, if the Power Chart is currently rendering in a responsive layout - False otherwise.
 605            """
 606            return "mobile" in self.find().get_attribute(name="class")
 607
 608        def open_date_range_selector_if_not_displayed(self) -> None:
 609            """
 610            Open the date range selector if it is not already displayed. No action is taken if the date range selector
 611            is already displayed.
 612            """
 613            self._date_range_selector.open_date_range_popover_or_modal_if_not_already_displayed()
 614
 615        def select_date_range_selector_tab(self, tab: DateRangeSelectorTab) -> None:
 616            """
 617            Select the supplied tab within the date range selector.
 618
 619            :param tab: The date range selector tab to click/select.
 620
 621            :raises TimeoutException: If the date range selector is not present.
 622            """
 623            self._date_range_selector.select_tab(tab=tab)
 624
 625        def select_realtime_unit(self, time_unit: DateRangeSelectorTimeUnit) -> None:
 626            """
 627            Select a realtime unit from the date range selector.
 628
 629            :param time_unit: The unit of time to select.
 630
 631            :raises TimeoutSelection: If the date range selector is not present.
 632            """
 633            self._date_range_selector.select_realtime_unit(time_unit=time_unit)

 635        def set_historical_day(self, numeric_day: Union[int, str]) -> None:
 636            """
 637            Select/click a day within the historical range selector. This requires that the date range selector already
 638            be displayed and the historical tab is already selected.
 639
 640            :param numeric_day: The numeric day to click within the historical range.
 641
 642            :raises TimeoutException: If the historical range selector is not present, or if the supplied day is
 643                invalid.
 644            """
 645            self._date_range_selector.select_date(date=PerspectiveDate(day=numeric_day))
 646
 647        def set_historical_month(self, month: str) -> None:
 648            """
 649            Select a month within the historical range selector. This requires that the date range selector already
 650            be displayed and the historical tab is already selected.
 651
 652            :param month: The month to select (eg: "January", not 1).
 653
 654            :raises TimeoutException: If the historical range selector is not present, or if the supplied month is not
 655                valid.
 656            """
 657            self._date_range_selector.select_date(date=PerspectiveDate(month=int(month)))
 658
 659        def set_historical_year(self, year: Union[int, str]) -> None:
 660            """
 661            Select a year from the dropdown in the Historical Range selector.
 662
 663            :param year: The year to select.
 664
 665            :raises TimeoutException: If the Historical Range Selector is not present.
 666            """
 667            self._date_range_selector.select_date(date=PerspectiveDate(year=int(year)))
 668
 669        def set_historical_range_and_apply(self, historical_range: HistoricalRange) -> None:
 670            """
 671            Open the date range selector, select values for a historical range, and then apply those changes.
 672
 673            :param historical_range: The historical range settings to apply, within a HistoricalRange object.
 674
 675            :raises AssertionError: If unsuccessful in applying the provided historical range.
 676            :raises TimeoutException: If the date range capabilities of the Power Chart are disabled.
 677            """
 678            self.open_date_range_selector_if_not_displayed()
 679            self.select_date_range_selector_tab(tab=DateRangeSelectorTab.HISTORICAL)
 680            self._date_range_selector.click_clear_in_historical_tab()
 681            self._date_range_selector.set_historical_range(historical_range=historical_range, apply=True)
 682
 683        def set_realtime_numeric_value(self, time_value: int) -> None:
 684            """
 685            Set the numeric (scalar) value in use by the realtime range.
 686
 687            :param time_value: The scalar value to use for the realtime range.
 688
 689            :raises AssertionError: If unsuccessful in applying the supplied time value.
 690            """
 691            self._date_range_selector.set_realtime_range(time_value=time_value)
 692
 693        def tag_browser_button_is_displayed(self) -> bool:
 694            """
 695            Determine if the Tag Browser button is displayed.
 696
 697            :returns: True if the Tag Browser button is currently displayed - False otherwise.
 698            """
 699            try:
 700                return self._tag_browser_button.find().is_displayed()
 701            except TimeoutException:
 702                return False
 703
 704        def _get_option_bar_button(self, option_bar_button: OptionBarButton) -> ComponentPiece:
 705            """
 706            Obtain one of the buttons available from the upper-right of the Power Chart.
 707
 708            :param option_bar_button: The Option Bar button to obtain.
 709            """
 710            _button_comp_piece = self._option_bar_buttons.get(option_bar_button.value)
 711            if not _button_comp_piece:
 712                _button_comp_piece = ComponentPiece(
 713                    locator=(By.ID, f"{self._GENERIC_ICON_STRING}{option_bar_button.value}"),
 714                    driver=self.driver,
 715                    parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
 716                    description=f"The {option_bar_button.value} button, found in the upper-right of the Power Chart.",
 717                    poll_freq=self.poll_freq)
 718                self._option_bar_buttons[option_bar_button.value] = _button_comp_piece
 719            return _button_comp_piece

 957        def click_point_in_color_picker(self) -> None:
 958            """
 959            Click the color picker displayed while editing any of the color settings for a pen. Requires that the
 960            picker already be visible as a result of clicking any of the available color dropdown items. Note that
 961            Selenium does not properly handle offsets for the color picker modal, so this function has limited use.
 962
 963            :raises TimeoutException: If the color picker is not present.
 964            """
 965            # TODO: Figure out why offsets don't work here
 966            ActionChains(driver=self.driver)\
 967                .move_to_element(
 968                    to_element=self._color_picker.find()
 969                )\
 970                .click()\
 971                .pause(1)\
 972                .perform()
 973
 974        def click_normal_state_stroke_color_dropdown(self) -> None:
 975            """
 976            Click the dropdown for the stroke color in the 'Normal State' section of the pen.
 977
 978            :raises TimeoutException: if not currently in the pen editing section of the Settings panel.
 979            """
 980            self._normal_state_stroke_color_dropdown.click()

 982        def click_tab(self, tab: Tab) -> None:
 983            """
 984            Click a tab of the Settings panel. Requires that the Settings panel already be open.
 985
 986            :param tab: The tab to click.
 987
 988            :raises TimeoutException: If the supplied tab is not present.
 989            """
 990            self._tab.set_locator(new_locator=(By.ID, f"{self._TAB_ID_GENERIC_STRING}{tab.value.lower()}"))
 991            self._tab.click()
 992            IAAssert.is_true(
 993                value=self.tab_is_active(tab=tab),
 994                failure_msg=f"Failed to select the {tab.value} tab.")
 995
 996        def close_settings_panel(self) -> None:
 997            """
 998            Close the Settings panel.
 999
1000            :raises AssertionError: If unsuccessful in closing the Settings panel.
1001            """
1002            if self.is_displayed():
1003                try:
1004                    self.click_chart_settings_breadcrumb_link()
1005                except TimeoutException:
1006                    pass
1007                try:
1008                    self._close_icon.click()
1009                except TimeoutException:
1010                    pass
1011            IAAssert.is_not_true(
1012                value=self.is_displayed(),
1013                failure_msg="Failed to close the Settings panel.")
1014

1017            Click the 'Delete' button available during the process of deleting a pen.

1020            """
1021            self._deletion_confirmation_button.click()

1164        def set_pen_control_column_display_state_in_settings_panel(
1165                self,
1166                pen_control_column: PenControlColumn,
1167                should_be_displayed: bool) -> None:
1168            """
1169            Set the display state of a column within the pen control table. Requires the Settings panel already be
1170            displayed.
1171
1172            :param pen_control_column: The column which will have its state set.
1173            :param should_be_displayed: If True, the column will be set to display - otherwise the column will be set to
1174                not be displayed.

1183                checkbox_component_piece=self._pen_control_column_checkbox, should_be_selected=should_be_displayed)

1185        def set_range_brush_column_display_state_in_settings_panel(
1186                self,
1187                range_brush_column: RangeBrushColumn,
1188                should_be_displayed: bool) -> None:
1189            """
1190            Set the display state of a column within the range brush table. Requires the Settings panel already be
1191            displayed.
1192
1193            :param range_brush_column: The column which will have its state set.
1194            :param should_be_displayed: If True, the column will be set to display - otherwise the column will be set to
1195                not be displayed.
1196
1197            :raises TimeoutException: If the Settings panel is not already displayed.
1198            """
1199            self.click_tab(tab=Tab.COLUMNS)

1204        def set_display_checkbox_state_by_pen_name(self, pen_name: str, should_be_selected: bool) -> None:
1205            """
1206            Set the display state of a pen listed in the Pens tab of the Settings panel. Requires the Settings panel
1207            already be displayed, and that the pen tab be displayed.
1208
1209            :param pen_name: The name of the pen which will have its state set.
1210            :param should_be_selected: If True, the pen will be set to display - otherwise, the pen will be set to not
1211                display.
1212
1213            :raises TimeoutException: If the Settings panel is not already displayed.
1214            """
1215            # requires special handling due to use of uncommon checkbox.
1216            if (self._get_pen_visibility_checkbox(
1217                    pen_name=pen_name).find().get_attribute('data-state') == "checked") != should_be_selected:
1218                self._get_pen_visibility_checkbox(pen_name=pen_name).click()
1219
1220        def set_pen_display_state_in_settings_panel(self, should_be_selected: bool) -> None:
1221            """
1222            Set the display state of a pen while the pen is being edited. This function expects that a pen is already
1223            being edited.
1224
1225            :param should_be_selected: If True, the pen will be set to display - otherwise, the pen will be set to not
1226                display.
1227
1228            :raises TimeoutException: If the Settings panel is not already displayed, or if we are not already editing
1229                a pen.
1230            """
1231            self._special_checkbox_handling(
1232                checkbox_component_piece=self._visible_checkbox, should_be_selected=should_be_selected)
1233
1234        def set_pen_enabled_state_in_settings_panel(self, should_be_enabled: bool) -> None:
1235            """
1236            Set the enabled state of a checkbox. The wording in the Power Chart is actually to "hide" the pen from the
1237            chart, so we reverse that logic inside this function. Requires that a pen already be in an "editing" state.
1238
1239            :param should_be_enabled: If True, the pen will NOT be hidden - otherwise we will set the pen to be hidden.
1240
1241            :raises TimeoutException: If the Settings panel is not already visible, or if a pen is not already being
1242                edited.
1243            """
1244            # This is counter-intuitive, but the checkbox is actually to "hide" the pen - so reverse the logic here.
1245            self._special_checkbox_handling(
1246                checkbox_component_piece=self._enabled_checkbox, should_be_selected=not should_be_enabled)
1247
1248        @classmethod
1249        def _special_checkbox_handling(
1250                cls, checkbox_component_piece: ComponentPiece, should_be_selected: bool) -> None:
1251            """
1252            Perform one-off handling of checkboxes within the Power Chart.
1253
1254            :param checkbox_component_piece: The ComponentPiece (not Checkbox) which defines the checkbox.
1255            :param should_be_selected: A True value dictates the checkbox should have a checked state.
1256
1257            :raises TimeoutException: If the checkbox can not be found.
1258            """
1259            svg = checkbox_component_piece.find().find_element(By.XPATH, '../*[name()="svg"]')
1260            if (svg.get_attribute("data-state") == "checked") != should_be_selected:
1261                svg.click()
1262
1263        def set_pen_name_field(self, updated_pen_name: str) -> None:
1264            """
1265            Set the name of a pen during editing.
1266
1267            :param updated_pen_name: The desired pen name.
1268
1269            :raises AssertionError: If unsuccessful in editing the name of the pen.
1270            :raises TimeoutException: If the Settings panel is not already visible, or if a pen is not already being
1271                edited.
1272            """
1273            current_text = self._update_pen_name_input_field.find().get_attribute("value")
1274            self._update_pen_name_input_field.click()
1275            self._update_pen_name_input_field.find().send_keys(
1276                ''.join(
1277                    [Keys.ARROW_LEFT for _ in current_text] +
1278                    [updated_pen_name] +
1279                    [Keys.DELETE for _ in current_text]))
1280            IAAssert.is_equal_to(
1281                actual_value=self._update_pen_name_input_field.find().get_attribute("value"),
1282                expected_value=updated_pen_name,
1283                failure_msg="Failed to modify the name of the pen while editing in the Settings panel.")
1284

1297            self._update_pen_path_input_field.find().send_keys(
1298                ''.join(
1299                    [Keys.ARROW_LEFT for _ in current_text] +
1300                    [updated_pen_path] +
1301                    [Keys.DELETE for _ in current_text]))

1329        def tab_is_active(self, tab: Tab) -> bool:
1330            """
1331            Determine if a tab is actively in use.
1332
1333            :param tab: The tab to check for.
1334
1335            :returns: True, if the supplied tab is currently the active tab in use - False otherwise.
1336
1337            raises TimeoutException: If the Settings panel is not already open, or if the Settings panel is not
1338                currently on the main tabbed layout section.
1339            """
1340            return self._active_tab.find().get_attribute(name="data-category") == tab.value.lower()

1342        def _get_range_brush_checkbox(self, range_brush_column: RangeBrushColumn) -> ComponentPiece:
1343            """
1344            Obtain a checkbox from the range brush section of the Columns tab.
1345
1346            :param range_brush_column: The column for which you would like the checkbox.
1347            """
1348            _checkbox = self._range_brush_column_checkboxes.get(range_brush_column.value)
1349            if not _checkbox:
1350                _checkbox = ComponentPiece(
1351                    locator=(
1352                        By.ID,
1353                        f"ia_powerChartComponent__settings__columnsTab__rangeSelection.{range_brush_column.value}"),
1354                    driver=self.driver,
1355                    parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
1356                    description=f"The {range_brush_column.value} checkbox within the Range Brush section of the "
1357                                f"Columns tab of the Settings Panel.",
1358                    poll_freq=self.poll_freq
1359                )
1360                self._range_brush_column_checkboxes[range_brush_column.value] = _checkbox
1361            return _checkbox

1363        def _get_pen_visibility_checkbox(self, pen_name: str) -> ComponentPiece:
1364            """
1365            Obtain the visibility checkbox for a row in the Pens tab of the Settings panel.
1366
1367            :param pen_name: The name of the pen for which you would like the visibility checkbox.
1368            """
1369            _checkbox = self._pen_visibility_checkboxes.get(pen_name)
1370            if not _checkbox:
1371                _checkbox = ComponentPiece(
1372                    locator=(By.CSS_SELECTOR, f'svg[data-pen-name="{pen_name}"]'),
1373                    driver=self.driver,
1374                    parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
1375                    description=f"The visibility checkbox to the left of the '{pen_name}' pen within the Pens tab of "
1376                                f"the Settings Panel,",
1377                    poll_freq=self.poll_freq)
1378                self._pen_visibility_checkboxes[pen_name] = _checkbox
1379            return _checkbox

1381        @classmethod
1382        def _click_checkbox_svg(cls, checkbox: ComponentPiece) -> bool:
1383            """
1384            Click the <svg> of a checkbox and report back on the success of the click.
1385
1386            :param checkbox: The ComponentPiece which defines the checkbox.
1387
1388            :returns: True, if the click event was successful - False otherwise.
1389
1390            :raises TimeoutException: if the checkbox could not be found.
1391            """
1392            try:
1393                checkbox.find().find_element(By.XPATH, '../*[name()="svg"]').click()
1394                return True
1395            except StaleElementReferenceException:
1396                return False

1455        def set_grid_y_axis_opacity(self, value: Union[float, str]) -> None:
1456            """
1457            Set the Y-axis opacity to be used by the grid for the axis currently being edited.
1458
1459            :param value: The desired value (0<=value<=1) to use for the opacity of the Y-axis of the grid.
1460
1461            :raises AssertionError: If unsuccessful in modifying the opacity in use by the Y-axis of the grid.
1462            :raises TimeoutException: If the Settings panel is not already displayed, or an axis is not already being
1463                edited.
1464            """
1465            self._grid_opacity.set_text(text=value)
1466            IAAssert.is_equal_to(
1467                actual_value=self._grid_opacity.wait_on_text_condition(
1468                    text_to_compare=value, condition=TextCondition.EQUALS),
1469                expected_value=value,
1470                as_type=str,
1471                failure_msg="Failed to set the opacity of the Y-axis of the grid while editing an axis.")

1511        def __init__(

1513                parent_locator_list: List[Tuple[By, str]],

1591        def click_pen_checkbox_by_name(self, pen_name: str) -> None:
1592            """
1593            Click the checkbox for a pen listed in the pen control table.
1594
1595            :param pen_name: The name of the pen for which you would like to click the accompanying checkbox.
1596
1597            :raises TimeoutException: If no pen with the supplied name is present.
1598            """
1599            self._pen_checkbox.set_locator(
1600                new_locator=(
1601                    By.CSS_SELECTOR, self._UNFORMATTED_PEN_VISIBILITY_CHECKBOX_SELECTOR_STRING.format(pen_name)))
1602            self._pen_checkbox.click()
1603
1604        def click_pencil_icon_for_pen(self, pen_name: str) -> None:
1605            """
1606            Click the pencil icon for a pen in the pen control table.
1607
1608            :param pen_name: The name of the pen for which you would like to click the accompanying pencil icon.
1609
1610            :raises IndexError: If no pen with the supplied name could be found.
1611            """
1612            pen_label_web_element = list(
1613                filter(
1614                    lambda e: e.text == pen_name,
1615                    self._pen_labels.find_all(
1616                        wait_timeout=1)))[0]
1617            IASelenium(
1618                driver=self.driver).hover_over_web_element(
1619                web_element=pen_label_web_element)
1620            self._edit_pen_icon.set_locator(
1621                new_locator=(By.CSS_SELECTOR, "div.tr.hovering svg.edit-pen-icon"))
1622            self._edit_pen_icon.click()

1624        def get_all_pen_names_from_pen_table(self) -> List[str]:
1625            """
1626            Obtain the names of all pens displayed in the pen control table.
1627
1628            :returns: A list which contains the name of every pen displayed in the pen control table.
1629
1630            :raises TimeoutException: If the pen control table is not present.
1631            """
1632            row_count = self.get_count_of_rows()
1633            pen_names = []
1634            for i in range(row_count):
1635                pen_names.append(self.get_row_data_by_row_index(zero_based_row_index=i)['penName'])
1636            return pen_names
1637
1638        def get_count_of_pen_fault_overlays(self) -> int:
1639            """
1640            Obtain a count of how many pens are currently displaying fault overlays.
1641
1642            :returns: A count of how many pens are currently displaying fault overlays.
1643            """
1644            try:
1645                return len(self._pen_overlay.find_all())
1646            except TimeoutException:
1647                return 0

1649        def get_column_headers_from_pen_table(self) -> List[str]:
1650            """
1651            Obtain the headers of the columns displayed in the pen control table. Ignores the selection column, as it
1652            contains no header text.
1653
1654            :returns: A list which contains the header of every column currently displayed in the pen control table.
1655
1656            :raises TimeoutException: If no pen control table is present.
1657            """
1658            return self.get_column_names_from_header()[1:]  # omit selection column

1662            Obtain a count of all pens listed in the pen control table.

1664            :returns: A count of every pen displayed in the pen control table.
1665
1666            :raises TimeoutException: If the pen control table is not present.

1670        def get_pen_checkbox_color(self, pen_name: str) -> str:
1671            """
1672            Obtain the color in use for a given pen. This color will always be the same as the line which is graphed.
1673
1674            :param pen_name: The name of the pen for which you would like the color of the accompanying checkbox.
1675
1676            :returns: The color in use by the checkbox of a pen.
1677

1679                pen control table is not present.

1683                    By.CSS_SELECTOR,
1684                    f'{self._UNFORMATTED_PEN_VISIBILITY_CHECKBOX_SELECTOR_STRING.format(pen_name)} > path'))
1685            return self._pen_checkbox.get_css_property(property_name=CSS.FILL)

1687        def pen_checkbox_is_active(self, pen_name: str) -> bool:
1688            """
1689            Determine if the checkbox of a pen is active (selected and/or checked are synonymous with active).
1690
1691            :param pen_name: The name of the pen for which we will check the accompanying checkbox.
1692
1693            :returns: True, if the checkbox for the specified pen is active/selected/checked.
1694
1695            :raises TimeoutException: If no pen with the supplied name is present in the pen control table, or if the
1696                pen control table is not present.
1697            """
1698            self._pen_checkbox.set_locator(
1699                new_locator=(
1700                    By.CSS_SELECTOR,
1701                    f'{self._UNFORMATTED_PEN_VISIBILITY_CHECKBOX_SELECTOR_STRING.format(pen_name)} > path'))
1702            return self._pen_checkbox.find().get_attribute('d') == self._PEN_CHECKBOX_SVG_CHECKED
1703
1704        def get_row_data_by_row_index(self, zero_based_row_index: int) -> dict:
1705            """
1706            Obtain the data of a specified row and return that data as a dictionary, where the keys of the dictionary
1707            are the column names.
1708
1709            :param zero_based_row_index: The zero-based index of the row you are targeting.
1710
1711            :returns: The row data as a dictionary, with the keys of the dictionary being the case-sensitive names of
1712                the columns.
1713            """
1714            row_data_as_dictionary = {}
1715            for cell in self._get_cell_components_by_row_index(zero_based_row_index=zero_based_row_index).find_all():
1716                row_data_as_dictionary[cell.get_attribute('data-column-id')] = cell.text
1717            row_data_as_dictionary.pop('toggle', None)
1718            return row_data_as_dictionary
1719
1720        def _get_cell_components_by_row_index(self, zero_based_row_index: int) -> ComponentPiece:
1721            """
1722            Obtain a ComponentPiece which describes how to locate the cells of a row of the pen control table.
1723
1724            :param zero_based_row_index: The zero-based index of the row these 'cells' would belong to.
1725            """
1726            cells = self._pen_control_table_cells_dict.get(zero_based_row_index)
1727            if not cells:
1728                cells = ComponentPiece(
1729                    locator=(By.CSS_SELECTOR, f'div.tr[data-row-index="{zero_based_row_index}"] div.tc'),
1730                    driver=self.driver,
1731                    parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
1732                    description=f"The cells from the {zero_based_row_index}th row in the pen control table.",
1733                    poll_freq=self.poll_freq)
1734                self._pen_control_table_cells_dict[zero_based_row_index] = cells
1735            return cells
1736
1737        def pen_control_column_is_displayed(
1738                self, pen_control_column: Union[PenControlColumn, RangeBrushColumn]) -> bool:
1739            """
1740            Determine if a pen control column is displayed.
1741
1742            :param pen_control_column: The pen control column or range brush column to check for the presence of.
1743
1744            :returns: True, if the supplied column is displayed - False otherwise.
1745            """
1746            try:
1747                return self._get_pen_control_table_column(pen_control_column=pen_control_column).find(1) is not None
1748            except TimeoutException:
1749                return False
1750
1751        def _get_pen_control_table_column(
1752                self, pen_control_column: Union[PenControlColumn, RangeBrushColumn]):
1753            pen_control_column = pen_control_column.value
1754            _column = self._pen_control_columns.get(pen_control_column)
1755            if not _column:
1756                _column = ComponentPiece(
1757                    locator=(By.CSS_SELECTOR, f'div.thc[data-column-id="{pen_control_column}"]'),
1758                    driver=self.driver,
1759                    parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
1760                    description=f"The '{pen_control_column}' column from the pen control table of the Power Chart.",
1761                    poll_freq=self.poll_freq)
1762                self._pen_control_columns[pen_control_column] = _column
1763            return _column

1765        def pen_table_is_expanded(self) -> bool:
1766            """
1767            Determine if the pen control table is expanded.
1768
1769            :returns: True, if the pen control table is currently expanded - False otherwise.
1770            """
1771            try:
1772                return (self.find() is not None) \
1773                       and ("collapse-icon" in self._pen_table_expand_collapse_svg.find().get_attribute("class"))
1774            except TimeoutException:
1775                return False

1777        def range_brush_column_is_displayed(self, range_brush_column: RangeBrushColumn) -> bool:
1778            """
1779            Determine if a range brush column is displayed in the pen control table.
1780
1781            :param range_brush_column: The range brush column for which we will check the display state.
1782
1783            :returns: True, if the supplied range brush column is displayed - False otherwise.
1784            """
1785            return self.pen_control_column_is_displayed(pen_control_column=range_brush_column)

1787        def remove_pen_by_name(self, pen_name: str) -> None:
1788            """
1789            Remove a pen from the pen control table (and therefore the Power Chart) via the pen control table.
1790
1791            :param pen_name: The name of the pen you would like to remove.
1792
1793            :raises AssertionError: If unsuccessful in removing the supplied pen from the Power Chart.
1794            :raises TimeoutException: If the pen control table is not present.
1795            """
1796            try:
1797                pen_label_web_element = list(filter(
1798                    lambda e: e.text == pen_name, self._pen_labels.find_all(wait_timeout=1)))[0]
1799                IASelenium(driver=self.driver).hover_over_web_element(web_element=pen_label_web_element)
1800                self._delete_pen_icon.set_locator(new_locator=(By.CSS_SELECTOR, "div.tr.hovering svg.delete-pen-icon"))
1801                self._delete_pen_icon.click()
1802                self._confirm_deletion_button.click()
1803            except IndexError:
1804                # no pen with name in controls
1805                pass
1806            IAAssert.does_not_contain(
1807                iterable=self.get_all_pen_names_from_pen_table(),
1808                expected_value=pen_name,
1809                failure_msg=f"The '{pen_name}' pen was still present in the pen control table after we attempted to "
1810                            f"remove it.")
1811
1812        def set_pen_visibility_on_pen_table(self, pen_name: str, should_be_visible: bool) -> None:
1813            """
1814            Set the display state (visibility) of a pen via the pen control table by interacting with the associated
1815            checkbox.
1816
1817            :param pen_name: The name of the pen which you would like to set the display state of.
1818            :param should_be_visible: If True, the checkbox will be set to active/selected/checked - otherwise the
1819                checkbox will be set to inactive/unselected/un-checked.
1820
1821            :raises AssertionError: If unsuccessful in setting the display state of the specified checkbox.
1822            :raises TimeoutException: if no pen with the supplied name is present, or if the pen control table is not
1823                present.
1824            """
1825            if self.pen_checkbox_is_active(pen_name=pen_name) != should_be_visible:
1826                self.click_pen_checkbox_by_name(pen_name=pen_name)
1827            IAAssert.is_equal_to(
1828                actual_value=self.pen_checkbox_is_active(pen_name=pen_name),
1829                expected_value=should_be_visible,
1830                failure_msg=f"Failed to set the display state (visibility) of the '{pen_name}' pen "
1831                            f"to {should_be_visible}.")
1832
1833        def toggle_pen_table_display(self) -> None:
1834            """
1835            Toggle the pen control table expansion state.
1836
1837            :raises TimeoutException: If the expand/collapse toggle icon is not present.
1838            """
1839            try:
1840                self._collapse_icon.click()
1841                self._expand_icon.find(wait_timeout=1)
1842            except TimeoutException:
1843                try:
1844                    self._expand_icon.click()
1845                    self._collapse_icon.find(wait_timeout=1)
1846                except TimeoutException as toe:
1847                    raise TimeoutException(
1848                        msg=f'Pen table collapse/expand icons could not be located for interaction.') from toe
1849
1850    class _PowerChartTagBrowser(CommonTagBrowseTree):
1851        """
1852        The Tag Browse Tree built into the Power Chart.
1853        """
1854        _ADD_TAG_BUTTON_LOCATOR = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, '.ia_button--primary')
1855        _CLOSE_ICON_LOCATOR = (By.ID, 'ia_powerChartComponent__tagBrowserContainer__closeIcon')
1856        _TAG_BROWSER_LOCATOR = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, 'div.ia_powerChartComponent__tagBrowserContainer')
1857        _TAG_BROWSER_OPEN_ICON_LOCATOR = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, 'span.show-tag-browser-icon')
1858        _RELOAD_ICON_LOCATOR = (By.ID, 'ia_powerChartComponent__tagBrowserContainer__reloadIcon')
1859
1860        def __init__(
1861                self,
1862                parent_locator_list: List[Tuple[By, str]],
1863                driver: WebDriver,
1864                poll_freq: float = 0.5):
1865            super().__init__(
1866                locator=self._TAG_BROWSER_LOCATOR,
1867                driver=driver,
1868                parent_locator_list=parent_locator_list,
1869                description="The Tag Browse Tree of the Power Chart.",
1870                poll_freq=poll_freq)
1871            self._add_tag_button = CommonButton(
1872                locator=self._ADD_TAG_BUTTON_LOCATOR,
1873                driver=driver,
1874                parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
1875                description="The 'Add Selected Tags' button at the bottom of the Tag Browse Tree.",
1876                poll_freq=poll_freq)
1877            self._close_icon = ComponentPiece(
1878                locator=self._CLOSE_ICON_LOCATOR,
1879                driver=driver,
1880                parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
1881                description="The arrow pointing left - and located in the upper-right of the Tag Browse Tree - which "
1882                            "collapses the Tag Browse Tree of the Power Chart.",
1883                poll_freq=poll_freq)
1884            self._reload_icon = ComponentPiece(
1885                locator=self._RELOAD_ICON_LOCATOR,
1886                driver=driver,
1887                parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
1888                description="The reload/refresh icon located in the upper-right of the Tag Browse Tree of the Power "
1889                            "Chart.",
1890                poll_freq=poll_freq)
1891
1892        def add_tags_to_chart(self, tag_paths: [str]) -> None:
1893            """
1894            Add tags to the Power Chart. Requires the Tag Browse Tree already be expanded. If all specified tags are
1895            already graphed, no action is taken, and the Tag Browse Tree will remain expanded.
1896
1897            :param tag_paths: A list of tag paths which describe the tags to add to the Power Chart graph as pens.
1898
1899            :raises TimeoutException: If any of the supplied paths does not map to a tag, or if the Tag Browse Tree is
1900                not present/expanded.
1901            """
1902            for tag_path in tag_paths:
1903                tag_name = self._split_item_label_path(tag_path)[-1]
1904                self._expand_tag_browser_tree_by_path(path=tag_path)
1905                try:
1906                    WebDriverWait(driver=self.driver, timeout=5).until(
1907                        IAec.function_returns_true(
1908                            custom_function=self._select_tag_to_be_added_later,
1909                            function_args={"tag_name": tag_name}))
1910                except TimeoutException as toe:
1911                    raise TimeoutException(msg=f"No tag found with a name of '{tag_name}'.") from toe
1912                # wait for Apply button to become enabled
1913                WebDriverWait(driver=self.driver, timeout=1).until(IAec.function_returns_true(
1914                    custom_function=self._add_tag_button.is_enabled, function_args={}))
1915                if self._add_tag_button.is_enabled():
1916                    # tag might already be displayed in the chart, so we might not need to add it
1917                    self._add_tag_button.click(binding_wait_time=1)
1918
1919        def click_reload_icon(self) -> None:
1920            """
1921            Click the reload icon of the Tag Browse Tree.
1922
1923            :raises TimeoutException: If the Tag Browse Tree is not expanded in the Power Chart.
1924            """
1925            self._reload_icon.click(binding_wait_time=1)
1926
1927        def collapse_if_expanded(self) -> None:
1928            """
1929            Collapse the Tag Browse Tree if it is currently expanded. If the Tag Browse Tree is already collapsed, then
1930            no action is taken.
1931            """
1932            if self.tag_browser_is_expanded():
1933                self._close_icon.click()
1934
1935        def is_displayed(self) -> bool:
1936            """
1937            Determine if the Tag Browse Tree is displayed.
1938
1939            :returns: True, if the Tag Browse Tree is currently displayed - False otherwise.
1940            """
1941            return self.tag_browser_is_expanded()
1942
1943        def is_in_responsive_mode(self) -> bool:
1944            """
1945            Determine if the Tag Browse Tree is in responsive mode.
1946
1947            :returns: True, if the Tag Browse Tree is currently rendering in responsive mode.
1948            """
1949            return "mobile" in self.find().get_attribute(name="class")
1950
1951        def tag_browser_is_expanded(self) -> bool:
1952            """
1953            Determine if the Tag Browse Tree is expanded.
1954
1955            :returns: True, if the tag Browse Tree is currently expanded - False otherwise.
1956            """
1957            try:
1958                return 'expanded' in self.find(wait_timeout=1).get_attribute('class')
1959            except TimeoutException:
1960                return False
1961
1962        def _expand_tag_browser_tree_by_path(self, path: str) -> None:
1963            """
1964            Expand the Tag Browse Tree structure based on a supplied tag path.
1965
1966            :param path: The path of a Tag as a slash-delimited string.
1967            """
1968            path_nodes = self._split_item_label_path(path)
1969            for i in path_nodes:
1970                try:
1971                    if self.item_label_exists_in_tree(item_label=i) and \
1972                            not self.item_is_expanded(item_label=i) \
1973                            and (path_nodes.index(i) != len(path_nodes)-1):
1974                        folder_index = self._get_index_of_item_in_tree(item_label=i)
1975                        self._folder_icons.find_all()[folder_index].click()
1976                        self.wait_on_binding(time_to_wait=1)
1977                        WebDriverWait(driver=self.driver, timeout=3, poll_frequency=self.poll_freq).until(
1978                            IAec.function_returns_true(
1979                                custom_function=self.item_is_expanded,
1980                                function_args={'item_label': i}))
1981                except TimeoutException as toe:
1982                    raise TimeoutException(
1983                        msg=f"Tag browser tree might not have expanded as expected.\nCheck that the provided "
1984                            f"path \'{path}\' is correct.") from toe
1985
1986        def _select_tag_to_be_added_later(self, tag_name: str) -> bool:
1987            """
1988            Select a singular tag for later addition to the Power Chart.
1989
1990            :param tag_name: The name of the tag to select now, for later addition to the Power Chart graph.
1991
1992            :returns: True, if the supplied tag name was selected successfully - False otherwise.
1993            """
1994            try:
1995                self.click_item_label(item_label=tag_name)
1996                return True
1997            except TimeoutException:
1998                return False

2000    def __init__(
2001            self,
2002            locator: Tuple[By, str],
2003            driver: WebDriver,
2004            parent_locator_list: Optional[List[Tuple[By, str]]] = None,
2005            wait_timeout: float = 10,
2006            description: Optional[str] = None,
2007            poll_freq: float = 0.5):
2008        super().__init__(
2009            locator=locator,
2010            driver=driver,
2011            parent_locator_list=parent_locator_list,
2012            wait_timeout=wait_timeout,
2013            description=description,
2014            poll_freq=poll_freq)
2015        self._footer = self._PowerChartFooter(
2016            parent_locator_list=self.locator_list, driver=driver, poll_freq=poll_freq)
2017        self._graph = self._PowerChartGraph(
2018            parent_locator_list=self.locator_list, driver=driver, poll_freq=poll_freq)
2019        self._header = self._PowerChartHeader(
2020            parent_locator_list=self.locator_list, driver=driver, poll_freq=poll_freq)
2021        self._pen_control_table = self._PowerChartTable(
2022            parent_locator_list=self.locator_list, driver=driver, poll_freq=poll_freq)
2023        self._settings_panel = self._PowerChartSettingsPanel(
2024            parent_locator_list=self.locator_list, driver=driver, poll_freq=poll_freq)
2025        self._tag_browser = self._PowerChartTagBrowser(
2026            parent_locator_list=self.locator_list, driver=driver, poll_freq=poll_freq)

2028    def add_tags_to_chart(self, tag_paths: [str]) -> None:
2029        """
2030        Add tags to the chart to be graphed as pens. This function will expand the Tag Browser if it is not already
2031        expanded, and will leave the Tag Browser expansion state as it was before this function was invoked.
2032
2033        :param tag_paths: A list containing the full tag paths of each tag to add.
2034
2035        :raises TimeoutException: If the Tag Browser button is not present, or if any supplied tag path does not
2036            identify a Tag to be added.
2037        """
2038        _original_state = self._tag_browser.tag_browser_is_expanded()
2039        if not _original_state:
2040            self._header.click_tag_browser_button()
2041        self._tag_browser.add_tags_to_chart(tag_paths=tag_paths)
2042        self.wait_on_binding(time_to_wait=2)  # wait for tags to be graphed
2043        if not _original_state:
2044            self._tag_browser.collapse_if_expanded()
2045
2046    def button_is_active(self, option_bar_button: OptionBarButton) -> bool:
2047        """
2048        Determine if an Option Bar button is active (selected/in-use).
2049
2050        :param option_bar_button: The Option Bar button to check the status of.
2051
2052        :returns: True, if the supplied Option Bar button is active - False otherwise.
2053        """
2054        return self._header.button_is_active(option_bar_button=option_bar_button)

2626    def select_historical_range(self, historical_range: HistoricalRange) -> None:
2627        """
2628        Apply the values of a HistoricalRange object to the Power Chart. This convenience function handles expansion,
2629        application, and confirmation of the supplied values.
2630
2631        :param historical_range: A HistoricalRange object which contains all of the information about the range to be
2632            selected.
2633
2634        :raises AssertionError: If unsuccessful in applying the provided range.
2635        """
2636        self._header.open_date_range_selector_if_not_displayed()
2637        self._header.select_date_range_selector_tab(tab=DateRangeSelectorTab.HISTORICAL)
2638        self._header.set_historical_month(month=historical_range.beginning_month)
2639        self._header.set_historical_year(year=historical_range.beginning_year)
2640        self._header.set_historical_day(numeric_day=historical_range.beginning_day)
2641        self._header.set_historical_month(month=historical_range.ending_month)
2642        self._header.set_historical_year(year=historical_range.ending_year)
2643        self._header.set_historical_day(numeric_day=historical_range.ending_day)
2644        self._header.apply_changes()
2645
2646    def select_realtime_range(self, time_value: int, time_unit: DateRangeSelectorTimeUnit) -> None:
2647        """
2648        Select the scalar value of time and the time unit to use for the realtime range of the Power Chart.
2649
2650        :param time_value: The scalar amount of time to apply.
2651        :param time_unit: The unit of time to apply.
2652
2653        :raises TimeoutException: If the range selector is not present.
2654        """
2655        self._header.open_date_range_selector_if_not_displayed()
2656        self._header.select_date_range_selector_tab(tab=DateRangeSelectorTab.REALTIME)
2657        self._header.set_realtime_numeric_value(time_value=time_value)
2658        self._header.select_realtime_unit(time_unit=time_unit)
2659        self._header.apply_changes()

class PowerChart(ignition_automation_tools.Components.BasicComponent.BasicPerspectiveComponent): 
  73class PowerChart(BasicPerspectiveComponent):

  76    class _PowerChartFooter(ComponentPiece):
  77        _FOOTER_LOCATOR = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, 'div.chart-footer')
  78
  79        def __init__(
  80                self,
  81                parent_locator_list: List[Tuple[By, str]],
  82                driver: WebDriver,
  83                description: Optional[str] = None,
  84                poll_freq: float = 0.5):
  85            super().__init__(
  86                locator=self._FOOTER_LOCATOR,
  87                driver=driver,
  88                parent_locator_list=parent_locator_list,
  89                description=description,
  90                poll_freq=poll_freq)
  91
  92        def is_in_responsive_mode(self) -> bool:
  93            """
  94            Determine if the Power Chart is in responsive mode.
  95
  96            :returns: True, if the Power Chart is currently displaying in a responsive layout - False otherwise.
  97            """
  98            try:
  99                return "mobile" in self.find().get_attribute(name="class")
 100            except TimeoutException as toe:
 101                raise TimeoutException(msg="Unable to locate the Power Chart as defined by its locator") from toe

 103    class _PowerChartGraph(ComponentPiece):
 104        _LINE_CHART_CONTAINER_LOCATOR = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, "div.main-chart-container")
 105        _GRAPHED_LINE_LOCATOR = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, f"g.ia_lineChart > g > g")
 106        _LINE_PATH_LOCATOR = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, "> path")
 107        _GRAPH_CONTAINER_LOCATOR = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, "g.chart-row")
 108        _LABEL_LOCATOR = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, "text.ia_powerChartComponent__timeAxis__values")
 109        _Y_AXIS_GRID_LOCATOR = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, "line.ia_powerChartComponent__yAxis__grid")
 110        _X_AXIS_GRID_LOCATOR = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, "line.ia_powerChartComponent__timeAxis__grid")
 111        _X_AXIS_LOCATOR = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, "line.ia_powerChartComponent__timeAxis__axis")
 112        _Y_AXIS_LABEL_LOCATOR = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, "text.ia_powerChartComponent__yAxis__label")
 113        _Y_AXIS_LOCATOR = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, "line.ia_powerChartComponent__yAxis__axis")
 114
 115        def __init__(
 116                self,
 117                parent_locator_list: List[Tuple[By, str]],
 118                driver: WebDriver,
 119                description: Optional[str] = None,
 120                poll_freq: float = 0.5):
 121            super().__init__(
 122                parent_locator_list=parent_locator_list,
 123                driver=driver,
 124                locator=self._LINE_CHART_CONTAINER_LOCATOR,
 125                description=description,
 126                poll_freq=poll_freq)
 127            self._row_container = ComponentPiece(
 128                locator=self._GRAPH_CONTAINER_LOCATOR,
 129                driver=driver,
 130                parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
 131                description="The container of all graphed lines in the chart.",
 132                poll_freq=poll_freq)
 133            self._graphed_line = ComponentPiece(
 134                locator=self._GRAPHED_LINE_LOCATOR,
 135                driver=driver,
 136                parent_locator_list=self._row_container.locator_list,
 137                description="The actual graphed line.",
 138                poll_freq=poll_freq)
 139            self._line_paths = ComponentPiece(
 140                parent_locator_list=self._graphed_line.locator_list,
 141                locator=self._LINE_PATH_LOCATOR,
 142                driver=driver,
 143                description="The <path> element within the line which describes the drawn path of the line.",
 144                poll_freq=poll_freq)
 145            self._time_axis_labels = ComponentPiece(
 146                locator=self._LABEL_LOCATOR,
 147                driver=driver,
 148                parent_locator_list=parent_locator_list,
 149                description="The labels of the time axis, usually found along the bottom of the graphed lines.",
 150                poll_freq=poll_freq)
 151            self._y_axis_grid_line = ComponentPiece(
 152                locator=self._Y_AXIS_GRID_LOCATOR,
 153                driver=driver,
 154                parent_locator_list=parent_locator_list,
 155                poll_freq=poll_freq)
 156            self._x_axis_grid_line = ComponentPiece(
 157                locator=self._X_AXIS_GRID_LOCATOR,
 158                driver=driver,
 159                parent_locator_list=parent_locator_list,
 160                poll_freq=poll_freq)
 161            self._x_axis = ComponentPiece(
 162                locator=self._X_AXIS_LOCATOR,
 163                driver=driver,
 164                parent_locator_list=parent_locator_list,
 165                description="The line which defines the bottom of the graphed area.",
 166                poll_freq=poll_freq)
 167            self._y_axis_label = ComponentPiece(
 168                locator=self._Y_AXIS_LABEL_LOCATOR,
 169                driver=driver,
 170                parent_locator_list=parent_locator_list,
 171                description="The labels of the Y axis, which can be found to either the left or right of the graphed "
 172                            "lines.",
 173                poll_freq=poll_freq)
 174            self._y_axis = ComponentPiece(
 175                locator=self._Y_AXIS_LOCATOR,
 176                driver=driver,
 177                parent_locator_list=parent_locator_list,
 178                description="The line which defines either the left or right border of the graph.",
 179                poll_freq=poll_freq)
 180
 181        def get_count_of_graphed_pens(self) -> int:
 182            """
 183            Obtain a count of pens which are displayed in the chart.
 184
 185            :returns: A count of pens currently rendered in the chart.
 186            """
 187            try:
 188                # each graphed pen has 2 <path> elements
 189                return int(len(self._line_paths.find_all(wait_timeout=1)) / 2)
 190            except TimeoutException:
 191                return 0
 192
 193        def get_displayed_time_axis_labels(self) -> List[str]:
 194            """
 195            Obtain the labels displayed on the X (time) axis.
 196
 197            :returns: A list which contains all currently displayed labels from the X (time) axis.
 198
 199            :raises TimeoutException: If no labels are displayed on the X (time) axis.
 200            """
 201            try:
 202                return [_.text for _ in self._time_axis_labels.find_all()]
 203            except TimeoutException as toe:
 204                raise TimeoutException(msg="No labels displayed for the Power Chart") from toe
 205
 206        def get_drawn_path(self, pen_checkbox_color_as_string: str) -> str:
 207            """
 208            Obtain the drawn path of a graphed pen. Useful for determining when a graphed pen has updated.
 209
 210            :param pen_checkbox_color_as_string: The color used to graph the pen for which you would like the drawn
 211                path.
 212
 213            :returns: A string which represents the actual graphed line of a pen.
 214
 215            :raises IndexError: If no graphed pen has the supplied color.
 216            :raises TimeoutException: If no pens are graphed.
 217            """
 218            try:
 219                return list(
 220                    filter(
 221                        lambda e: e.value_of_css_property(CSS.STROKE.value) == pen_checkbox_color_as_string,
 222                        self._line_paths.find_all()))[0].get_attribute("d")
 223            except TimeoutException as toe:
 224                raise TimeoutException(msg="No pens are currently graphed.") from toe
 225            except IndexError as ie:
 226                raise IndexError(f"No pen graphed with a color of '{pen_checkbox_color_as_string}'.") from ie
 227
 228        def get_x_axis_html_class(self) -> str:
 229            """
 230            Obtain the HTML class of the X axis.
 231
 232            :returns: The class of the X axis as it exists in the DOM.
 233
 234            :raises TimeoutException: If no X axis is present.
 235            """
 236            try:
 237                return self._x_axis.find().get_attribute(name="class")
 238            except TimeoutException as toe:
 239                raise TimeoutException(msg="No X axis present.") from toe
