 299        def click_and_drag_chart(self, x_offset: int = 0, y_offset: int = 0) -> None:
 300            """
 301            Blindly click within the Power Chart and then drag some number of pixels before releasing the click event.
 302
 303            :param x_offset: The number of pixels to the right of the upper left corner to click.
 304            :param y_offset: The number of pixels down from the upper left corner to click.
 305            """
 306            ActionChains(driver=self.driver) \
 307                .click_and_hold(on_element=self.find()) \
 308                .move_by_offset(xoffset=x_offset, yoffset=y_offset) \
 309                .release() \
 310                .perform()
 311            self.wait_on_binding(time_to_wait=1)
 312
 313        def get_count_of_x_axis_grid_lines(self, _already_attempted=False) -> int:
 314            """
 315            Obtain a count of lines displayed on the X axis.
 316
 317            :param _already_attempted: Used internally to re-try in the event the Power Chart updates.
 318
 319            :returns: A count of vertical lines currently displayed on the X axis of the Power Chart.
 320            """
 321            try:
 322                return len(self._x_axis_grid_line.find_all())
 323            except TimeoutException:
 324                return 0
 325            except StaleElementReferenceException as sere:
 326                if not _already_attempted:
 327                    return self.get_count_of_x_axis_grid_lines(
 328                        _already_attempted=True)
 329                else:
 330                    raise sere
 331
 332        def get_count_of_y_axis_grid_lines(self, _already_attempted=False) -> int:
 333            """
 334            Obtain a count of lines displayed on the Y axis.
 335
 336            :param _already_attempted: Used internally to re-try in the event the Power Chart updates.
 337
 338            :returns: A count of horizontal lines currently displayed on the Y axis of the Power Chart.
 339            """
 340            try:
 341                return len(self._y_axis_grid_line.find_all())
 342            except TimeoutException:
 343                return 0
 344            except StaleElementReferenceException as sere:
 345                if not _already_attempted:
 346                    return self.get_count_of_y_axis_grid_lines(
 347                        _already_attempted=True)
 348                else:
 349                    raise sere
 350
 351        def get_css_property_from_x_axis_grid(self, property_name: Union[CSSPropertyValue, str]) -> str:
 352            """
 353            Obtain the value of a CSS property from the grid of the X axis.
 354
 355            :param property_name: The name of the property you want to value of.
 356
 357            :returns: The value of the requested CSS property from the X axis grid.
 358
 359            :raises TimeoutException: If no X axis grid is present.
 360            """
 361            try:
 362                return self._x_axis_grid_line.get_css_property(property_name=property_name)
 363            except StaleElementReferenceException:
 364                return self.get_css_property_from_x_axis_grid(property_name=property_name)
 365            except TimeoutException as toe:
 366                raise TimeoutException(
 367                    msg="No grid line was found for the X axis.") from toe
 368
 369        def get_css_property_from_y_axis_grid(self, property_name: Union[CSSPropertyValue, str]) -> str:
 370            """
 371            Obtain the value of a CSS property from the grid of the Y axis.
 372
 373            :param property_name: The name of the property you want to value of.
 374
 375            :returns: The value of the requested CSS property from the Y axis grid.
 376
 377            :raises TimeoutException: If no Y axis grid is present.
 378            """
 379            try:
 380                return self._y_axis_grid_line.get_css_property(property_name=property_name)
 381            except StaleElementReferenceException:
 382                return self.get_css_property_from_y_axis_grid(
 383                    property_name=property_name)
 384            except TimeoutException as toe:
 385                raise TimeoutException(
 386                    msg="No grid line was found for the Y axis.") from toe
 387
 388        def line_is_displayed_by_color(self, pen_checkbox_color_as_str: str) -> bool:
 389            """
 390            Determine if a line is graphed.
 391
 392            :param pen_checkbox_color_as_str: The color to look for in the graph. This value MUST be supplied in the
 393                same form as the browser in use would return a color value. It is recommended to avoid supplying
 394                hard-coded colors and instead supply values retrieved from the browser.
 395
 396            :returns: True, if any graphed line uses the supplied color - False otherwise.
 397            """
 398            try:
 399                return len(
 400                    list(
 401                        filter(
 402                            lambda e: e.value_of_css_property(CSS.STROKE.value) == pen_checkbox_color_as_str,
 403                            self._line_paths.find_all()))) == 1
 404            except TimeoutException:
 405                return False
 406
 407        def set_range_brush_basic(self) -> None:
 408            """
 409            Applies the range brush to the graph via a short drag event.
 410            """
 411            self.click_and_drag_chart(x_offset=100, y_offset=0)

 413    class _PowerChartHeader(ComponentPiece):
 414        """
 415        The header of the Power Chart, where the Option Bar Buttons live, as well as the range selector.
 416        """
 417        # TODO remove after IGN-5195
 418        _FULLSCREEN_BUTTON_ACTIVE_PATH = "M5 16h3v3h2v-5H5v2zm3-8H5v2h5V5H8v3zm6 11h2v-3h3v-2h-5v5zm2-11V5h-2v5h5V8h-3z"

 420        _GENERIC_ICON_STRING = "ia_powerChartComponent__icon__"
 421        _BUTTON_ACTIVE_CLASS = "ia_powerChartComponent__icon--active"
 422        _HEADER_LOCATOR = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, 'div.chart-header')
 423        _FULLSCREEN_BUTTON_ID_SUFFIX = "fullscreen"
 424        _TAG_BROWSER_BUTTON_LOCATOR = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, "div.tag-browser-icon-and-timerange span.show-tag-browser-icon")

 427        def __init__(
 428                self,
 429                parent_locator_list: List[Tuple[By, str]],
 430                driver: WebDriver,
 431                poll_freq: float = 0.5):
 432            super().__init__(
 433                locator=self._HEADER_LOCATOR,
 434                driver=driver,
 435                parent_locator_list=parent_locator_list,
 436                poll_freq=poll_freq)
 437            self._tag_browser_button = ComponentPiece(
 438                locator=self._TAG_BROWSER_BUTTON_LOCATOR,
 439                driver=self.driver,
 440                parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
 441                description="The button used to expand the Tag Browser Tree.",
 442                poll_freq=poll_freq)
 443            self._fullscreen_button_path = ComponentPiece(
 444                locator=(By.CSS_SELECTOR, f"#{self._GENERIC_ICON_STRING}{self._FULLSCREEN_BUTTON_ID_SUFFIX} path"),
 445                driver=self.driver,
 446                parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
 447                description="The <path> element of the fullscreen button.",
 448                poll_freq=poll_freq)
 449            self._date_range_selector = CommonDateRangeSelector(
 450                driver=driver,
 451                parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
 452                description="The Date Range Selector of the Power Chart. If enabled, this is found in the upper-left "
 453                            "of the Power Chart.",
 454                poll_freq=poll_freq)
 455            self._option_bar_buttons = {}
 456            self._title = ComponentPiece(
 457                locator=self._TITLE_LOCATOR,
 458                driver=driver,
 459                parent_locator_list=parent_locator_list,
 460                description="The title of the Power Chart. If configured, this will be found on the left side of the "
 461                            "Power Chart, between the toolbar area of the Power Chart and the graph itself.",
 462                poll_freq=poll_freq)

 464        def apply_changes(self) -> None:
 465            """
 466            Click the Apply button in the range selector.
 467
 468            :raises TimeoutException: If the range selector is not present, or if the Apply button is not present.
 469            """
 470            self._date_range_selector.apply_changes()
 471
 472        def button_is_active(self, option_bar_button: OptionBarButton) -> bool:
 473            """
 474            Determine if an Option Bar button is active (selected/in-use).
 475
 476            :param option_bar_button: The Option Bar button to check the status of.
 477
 478            :returns: True, if the supplied Option Bar button is active - False otherwise.
 479            """
 480            try:
 481                if option_bar_button == OptionBarButton.FULL_SCREEN:
 482                    # special handling for fullscreen button
 483                    return self._FULLSCREEN_BUTTON_ACTIVE_PATH \
 484                        == self._fullscreen_button_path.find().get_attribute(
 485                            name="d")
 486                else:
 487                    return self._BUTTON_ACTIVE_CLASS in self._get_option_bar_button(
 488                        option_bar_button=option_bar_button).find().get_attribute("class")
 489            except TimeoutException as toe:
 490                raise TimeoutException(
 491                    msg=f"No {option_bar_button.value} button found among the Option Bar buttons.") from toe
 492
 493        def button_is_displayed(self, option_bar_button: OptionBarButton) -> bool:
 494            """
 495            Determine if an Option Bar button is displayed.
 496
 497            :param option_bar_button: The Option Bar button we will check.
 498
 499            :returns: True, if the supplied Option Bar button is displayed - False otherwise.
 500            """
 501            try:
 502                return self._get_option_bar_button(option_bar_button=option_bar_button).find().is_displayed()
 503            except TimeoutException:
 504                return False

 636        def set_historical_day(self, numeric_day: Union[int, str]) -> None:
 637            """
 638            Select/click a day within the historical range selector. This requires that the date range selector already
 639            be displayed and the historical tab is already selected.
 640
 641            :param numeric_day: The numeric day to click within the historical range.
 642
 643            :raises TimeoutException: If the historical range selector is not present, or if the supplied day is
 644                invalid.
 645            """

 648        def set_historical_month(self, month: str) -> None:
 649            """
 650            Select a month within the historical range selector. This requires that the date range selector already
 651            be displayed and the historical tab is already selected.
 652
 653            :param month: The month to select (eg: "January", not 1).
 654
 655            :raises TimeoutException: If the historical range selector is not present, or if the supplied month is not
 656                valid.
 657            """

 661            """

 670        def set_historical_range_and_apply(self, historical_range: HistoricalRange) -> None:
 671            """
 672            Open the date range selector, select values for a historical range, and then apply those changes.
 673
 674            :param historical_range: The historical range settings to apply, within a HistoricalRange object.
 675
 676            :raises AssertionError: If unsuccessful in applying the provided historical range.
 677            :raises TimeoutException: If the date range capabilities of the Power Chart are disabled.
 678            """
 679            self.open_date_range_selector_if_not_displayed()
 680            self.select_date_range_selector_tab(tab=DateRangeSelectorTab.HISTORICAL)
 681            self._date_range_selector.click_clear_in_historical_tab()
 682            self._date_range_selector.set_historical_range(historical_range=historical_range, apply=True)
 683
 684        def set_realtime_numeric_value(self, time_value: int) -> None:
 685            """
 686            Set the numeric (scalar) value in use by the realtime range.
 687
 688            :param time_value: The scalar value to use for the realtime range.
 689
 690            :raises AssertionError: If unsuccessful in applying the supplied time value.
 691            """
 692            self._date_range_selector.set_realtime_range(time_value=time_value)

 695            """
 696            Determine if the Tag Browser button is displayed.
 697
 698            :returns: True if the Tag Browser button is currently displayed - False otherwise.
 699            """
 700            try:
 701                return self._tag_browser_button.find().is_displayed()
 702            except TimeoutException:
 703                return False

 705        def _get_option_bar_button(self, option_bar_button: OptionBarButton) -> ComponentPiece:
 706            """
 707            Obtain one of the buttons available from the upper-right of the Power Chart.
 708
 709            :param option_bar_button: The Option Bar button to obtain.
 710            """
 711            _button_comp_piece = self._option_bar_buttons.get(option_bar_button.value)
 712            if not _button_comp_piece:
 713                _button_comp_piece = ComponentPiece(
 714                    locator=(By.ID, f"{self._GENERIC_ICON_STRING}{option_bar_button.value}"),
 715                    driver=self.driver,
 716                    parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
 717                    description=f"The {option_bar_button.value} button, found in the upper-right of the Power Chart.",
 718                    poll_freq=self.poll_freq)
 719                self._option_bar_buttons[option_bar_button.value] = _button_comp_piece
 720            return _button_comp_piece

 958        def click_point_in_color_picker(self) -> None:
 959            """
 960            Click the color picker displayed while editing any of the color settings for a pen. Requires that the
 961            picker already be visible as a result of clicking any of the available color dropdown items. Note that
 962            Selenium does not properly handle offsets for the color picker modal, so this function has limited use.
 963
 964            :raises TimeoutException: If the color picker is not present.
 965            """
 966            # TODO: Figure out why offsets don't work here
 967            ActionChains(driver=self.driver)\
 968                .move_to_element(
 969                    to_element=self._color_picker.find()
 970                )\
 971                .click()\
 972                .pause(1)\
 973                .perform()

 975        def click_normal_state_stroke_color_dropdown(self) -> None:
 976            """
 977            Click the dropdown for the stroke color in the 'Normal State' section of the pen.
 978
 979            :raises TimeoutException: if not currently in the pen editing section of the Settings panel.
 980            """

 983        def click_tab(self, tab: Tab) -> None:
 984            """
 985            Click a tab of the Settings panel. Requires that the Settings panel already be open.
 986
 987            :param tab: The tab to click.
 988
 989            :raises TimeoutException: If the supplied tab is not present.
 990            """
 991            self._tab.set_locator(new_locator=(By.ID, f"{self._TAB_ID_GENERIC_STRING}{tab.value.lower()}"))
 992            self._tab.click()
 993            IAAssert.is_true(
 994                value=self.tab_is_active(tab=tab),
 995                failure_msg=f"Failed to select the {tab.value} tab.")
 996
 997        def close_settings_panel(self) -> None:
 998            """
 999            Close the Settings panel.
1000
1001            :raises AssertionError: If unsuccessful in closing the Settings panel.
1002            """
1003            if self.is_displayed():
1004                try:
1005                    self.click_chart_settings_breadcrumb_link()
1006                except TimeoutException:
1007                    pass
1008                try:
1009                    self._close_icon.click()
1010                except TimeoutException:
1011                    pass
1012            IAAssert.is_not_true(
1013                value=self.is_displayed(),
1014                failure_msg="Failed to close the Settings panel.")
1015

1024        def click_trash_can_icon_for_pen(self, pen_name: str) -> None:
1025            """

1027            are further actions to take after this.

1036        def _get_delete_icon_by_pen_name(self, pen_name: str) -> ComponentPiece:
1037            """
1038            Obtain the trash can icon from the Tag History Pens tab for the supplied pen.
1039
1040            :param pen_name: The name of the pen to target.
1041            """
1042            _icon = self._delete_icons_dict.get(pen_name)
1043            if not _icon:
1044                _icon = ComponentPiece(
1045                    locator=(
1046                        By.CSS_SELECTOR,
1047                        f'svg[id^="ia_powerChartComponent__settings__pensTab__deleteIcon"][data-pen-name="{pen_name}"'),
1048                    driver=self.driver,
1049                    parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
1050                    description=f"The trash can icon for the '{pen_name}' pen in the Pens tab of the Settings Panel.",
1051                    poll_freq=self.poll_freq)
1052                self._delete_icons_dict[pen_name] = _icon
1053            return _icon

1097        def get_count_of_displayed_pens(self) -> int:
1098            """
1099            Obtain a count of how many pens are currently listed in the Pens tab of the Settings panel. Requires that
1100            the Settings panel already be displayed and the Pens tab be selected.
1101
1102            :returns: A numeric count of the pens listed in the Pens tab of the Settings Panel.
1103            """
1104            try:
1105                return len(self._pen_rows.find_all())
1106            except TimeoutException:
1107                return 0

1109        def get_displayed_pen_names(self) -> List[str]:
1110            """
1111            Obtain a list of all pen names displayed in the Pens tab of the Settings panel. Requires that the Settings
1112            panel already be displayed and the Pens tab be selected.
1113
1114            :returns: A list which contains all pen names displayed in the Pens tab of the Settings panel.
1115            """
1116            try:
1117                return [_.text for _ in self._pen_rows.find_all()]
1118            except TimeoutException:
1119                return []

1121        def get_displayed_tab_names(self) -> List[str]:
1122            """

1124            displayed.

1126            :returns: A list which contains the names of all tabs displayed in the Settings panel.

1143        def is_displayed(self) -> bool:
1144            """
1145            Determine if the Settings panel is displayed.
1146
1147            :returns: True, if the Settings panel is currently open/displayed/expanded - False otherwise.
1148            """
1149            try:
1150                return self.find(wait_timeout=1).is_displayed() and "expanded" in self.find().get_attribute("class")
1151            except TimeoutException:
1152                return False
1153
1154        def pen_settings_are_displayed(self) -> bool:
1155            """
1156            Determine if the Pen settings panel is displayed.
1157
1158            :returns: True, if the inputs used to edit a pen are currently displayed - False otherwise.
1159            """
1160            try:
1161                return self._update_pen_name_input_field.find(wait_timeout=1) is not None
1162            except TimeoutException:
1163                return False

1165        def set_pen_control_column_display_state_in_settings_panel(
1166                self,
1167                pen_control_column: PenControlColumn,
1168                should_be_displayed: bool) -> None:
1169            """
1170            Set the display state of a column within the pen control table. Requires the Settings panel already be
1171            displayed.
1172
1173            :param pen_control_column: The column which will have its state set.
1174            :param should_be_displayed: If True, the column will be set to display - otherwise the column will be set to
1175                not be displayed.
1176
1177            :raises TimeoutException: If the Settings panel is not already displayed.
1178            """
1179            self.click_tab(tab=Tab.COLUMNS)
1180            self._pen_control_column_checkbox.set_locator(
1181                new_locator=(
1182                    By.ID, f"ia_powerChartComponent__settings__columnsTab__penControl.{pen_control_column.value}"))
1183            self._special_checkbox_handling(
1184                checkbox_component_piece=self._pen_control_column_checkbox, should_be_selected=should_be_displayed)
1185
1186        def set_range_brush_column_display_state_in_settings_panel(
1187                self,
1188                range_brush_column: RangeBrushColumn,
1189                should_be_displayed: bool) -> None:
1190            """
1191            Set the display state of a column within the range brush table. Requires the Settings panel already be
1192            displayed.
1193
1194            :param range_brush_column: The column which will have its state set.
1195            :param should_be_displayed: If True, the column will be set to display - otherwise the column will be set to
1196                not be displayed.
1197
1198            :raises TimeoutException: If the Settings panel is not already displayed.
1199            """
1200            self.click_tab(tab=Tab.COLUMNS)
1201            self._special_checkbox_handling(
1202                checkbox_component_piece=self._get_range_brush_checkbox(range_brush_column=range_brush_column),
1203                should_be_selected=should_be_displayed)

1205        def set_display_checkbox_state_by_pen_name(self, pen_name: str, should_be_selected: bool) -> None:
1206            """
1207            Set the display state of a pen listed in the Pens tab of the Settings panel. Requires the Settings panel
1208            already be displayed, and that the pen tab be displayed.
1209
1210            :param pen_name: The name of the pen which will have its state set.
1211            :param should_be_selected: If True, the pen will be set to display - otherwise, the pen will be set to not
1212                display.
1213
1214            :raises TimeoutException: If the Settings panel is not already displayed.
1215            """
1216            # requires special handling due to use of uncommon checkbox.
1217            if (self._get_pen_visibility_checkbox(
1218                    pen_name=pen_name).find().get_attribute('data-state') == "checked") != should_be_selected:
1219                self._get_pen_visibility_checkbox(pen_name=pen_name).click()
1220
1221        def set_pen_display_state_in_settings_panel(self, should_be_selected: bool) -> None:
1222            """
1223            Set the display state of a pen while the pen is being edited. This function expects that a pen is already
1224            being edited.
1225
1226            :param should_be_selected: If True, the pen will be set to display - otherwise, the pen will be set to not
1227                display.
1228
1229            :raises TimeoutException: If the Settings panel is not already displayed, or if we are not already editing
1230                a pen.
1231            """
1232            self._special_checkbox_handling(
1233                checkbox_component_piece=self._visible_checkbox, should_be_selected=should_be_selected)
1234
1235        def set_pen_enabled_state_in_settings_panel(self, should_be_enabled: bool) -> None:
1236            """
1237            Set the enabled state of a checkbox. The wording in the Power Chart is actually to "hide" the pen from the
1238            chart, so we reverse that logic inside this function. Requires that a pen already be in an "editing" state.
1239
1240            :param should_be_enabled: If True, the pen will NOT be hidden - otherwise we will set the pen to be hidden.
1241
1242            :raises TimeoutException: If the Settings panel is not already visible, or if a pen is not already being
1243                edited.
1244            """
1245            # This is counter-intuitive, but the checkbox is actually to "hide" the pen - so reverse the logic here.
1246            self._special_checkbox_handling(
1247                checkbox_component_piece=self._enabled_checkbox, should_be_selected=not should_be_enabled)
1248
1249        @classmethod
1250        def _special_checkbox_handling(
1251                cls, checkbox_component_piece: ComponentPiece, should_be_selected: bool) -> None:
1252            """
1253            Perform one-off handling of checkboxes within the Power Chart.
1254
1255            :param checkbox_component_piece: The ComponentPiece (not Checkbox) which defines the checkbox.
1256            :param should_be_selected: A True value dictates the checkbox should have a checked state.
1257
1258            :raises TimeoutException: If the checkbox can not be found.
1259            """
1260            svg = checkbox_component_piece.find().find_element(By.XPATH, '../*[name()="svg"]')
1261            if (svg.get_attribute("data-state") == "checked") != should_be_selected:
1262                svg.click()
1263
1264        def set_pen_name_field(self, updated_pen_name: str) -> None:
1265            """
1266            Set the name of a pen during editing.
1267
1268            :param updated_pen_name: The desired pen name.
1269
1270            :raises AssertionError: If unsuccessful in editing the name of the pen.
1271            :raises TimeoutException: If the Settings panel is not already visible, or if a pen is not already being
1272                edited.
1273            """
1274            current_text = self._update_pen_name_input_field.find().get_attribute("value")
1275            self._update_pen_name_input_field.click()
1276            self._update_pen_name_input_field.find().send_keys(
1277                ''.join(
1278                    [Keys.ARROW_LEFT for _ in current_text] +
1279                    [updated_pen_name] +
1280                    [Keys.DELETE for _ in current_text]))
1281            IAAssert.is_equal_to(
1282                actual_value=self._update_pen_name_input_field.find().get_attribute("value"),
1283                expected_value=updated_pen_name,
1284                failure_msg="Failed to modify the name of the pen while editing in the Settings panel.")
1285
1286        def set_pen_path_field(self, updated_pen_path: str) -> None:
1287            """
1288            Set the path of a pen during editing.
1289
1290            :param updated_pen_path: The desired pen path to use.
1291
1292            :raises AssertionError: If unsuccessful in editing the path of the pen.
1293            :raises TimeoutException: If the Settings panel is not already visible, or if a pen is not already being
1294                edited.
1295            """
1296            current_text = self._update_pen_path_input_field.find().get_attribute("value")
1297            self._update_pen_path_input_field.click()
1298            self._update_pen_path_input_field.find().send_keys(
1299                ''.join(
1300                    [Keys.ARROW_LEFT for _ in current_text] +
1301                    [updated_pen_path] +
1302                    [Keys.DELETE for _ in current_text]))
1303            IAAssert.is_equal_to(
1304                actual_value=self._update_pen_path_input_field.find().get_attribute("value"),
1305                expected_value=updated_pen_path,
1306                failure_msg="Failed to modify the path of the pen while editing in the Settings panel.")
1307
1308        def set_pen_stroke_color(self, hex_desired_color: str) -> None:
1309            """
1310            Set the stroke color of a pen during editing.
1311
1312            :param hex_desired_color: The color to use for the stroke of the pen, in hex format.
1313
1314            :raises AssertionError: If unsuccessful in editing the stroke color of the pen.
1315            :raises TimeoutException: If the Settings panel is not already visible, or if a pen is not already being
1316                edited.
1317            """
1318            self._normal_state_stroke_color_dropdown.click()
1319            current_text = self._shared_color_modal_input.find().get_attribute("value")
1320            self._shared_color_modal_input.find().send_keys(
1321                ''.join(
1322                    [Keys.ARROW_LEFT for _ in current_text] +
1323                    [hex_desired_color] +
1324                    [Keys.DELETE for _ in current_text]))
1325            IAAssert.is_equal_to(
1326                actual_value=self._shared_color_modal_input.find().get_attribute("value"),
1327                expected_value=hex_desired_color,
1328                failure_msg="Failed to modify the stroke of the pen while editing in the Settings panel.")
1329
1330        def tab_is_active(self, tab: Tab) -> bool:
1331            """
1332            Determine if a tab is actively in use.
1333
1334            :param tab: The tab to check for.
1335
1336            :returns: True, if the supplied tab is currently the active tab in use - False otherwise.
1337
1338            raises TimeoutException: If the Settings panel is not already open, or if the Settings panel is not
1339                currently on the main tabbed layout section.
1340            """
1341            return self._active_tab.find().get_attribute(name="data-category") == tab.value.lower()

1343        def _get_range_brush_checkbox(self, range_brush_column: RangeBrushColumn) -> ComponentPiece:
1344            """
1345            Obtain a checkbox from the range brush section of the Columns tab.
1346
1347            :param range_brush_column: The column for which you would like the checkbox.
1348            """
1349            _checkbox = self._range_brush_column_checkboxes.get(range_brush_column.value)
1350            if not _checkbox:
1351                _checkbox = ComponentPiece(
1352                    locator=(
1353                        By.ID,
1354                        f"ia_powerChartComponent__settings__columnsTab__rangeSelection.{range_brush_column.value}"),
1355                    driver=self.driver,
1356                    parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
1357                    description=f"The {range_brush_column.value} checkbox within the Range Brush section of the "
1358                                f"Columns tab of the Settings Panel.",
1359                    poll_freq=self.poll_freq
1360                )
1361                self._range_brush_column_checkboxes[range_brush_column.value] = _checkbox
1362            return _checkbox

1377                                f"the Settings Panel,",
1378                    poll_freq=self.poll_freq)
1379                self._pen_visibility_checkboxes[pen_name] = _checkbox

1382        @classmethod
1383        def _click_checkbox_svg(cls, checkbox: ComponentPiece) -> bool:
1384            """
1385            Click the <svg> of a checkbox and report back on the success of the click.
1386
1387            :param checkbox: The ComponentPiece which defines the checkbox.
1388
1389            :returns: True, if the click event was successful - False otherwise.
1390
1391            :raises TimeoutException: if the checkbox could not be found.
1392            """
1393            try:
1394                checkbox.find().find_element(By.XPATH, '../*[name()="svg"]').click()
1395                return True
1396            except StaleElementReferenceException:
1397                return False

1434        def set_grid_y_axis_color(self, hex_desired_color: str) -> None:
1435            """
1436            Set the Y-axis color to be used by the grid for the axis currently being edited.
1437
1438            :param hex_desired_color: The color (in hex format) to use for the Y-axis of the grid.
1439
1440            :raises AssertionError: If unsuccessful in modifying the color in use by the Y-axis of the grid.
1441            :raises TimeoutException: If the Settings panel is not already displayed, or an axis is not already being
1442                edited.
1443            """
1444            self._grid_color_picker_dropdown.click()
1445            current_text = self._shared_color_modal_input.find().get_attribute("value")
1446            self._shared_color_modal_input.find().send_keys(
1447                ''.join(
1448                    [Keys.ARROW_LEFT for _ in current_text] +
1449                    [hex_desired_color] +
1450                    [Keys.DELETE for _ in current_text]))
1451            IAAssert.is_equal_to(
1452                actual_value=self._shared_color_modal_input.find().get_attribute("value"),
1453                expected_value=hex_desired_color,
1454                failure_msg="Failed to set the color of the Y-axis of the grid while editing an axis.")
1455
1456        def set_grid_y_axis_opacity(self, value: Union[float, str]) -> None:
1457            """
1458            Set the Y-axis opacity to be used by the grid for the axis currently being edited.
1459
1460            :param value: The desired value (0<=value<=1) to use for the opacity of the Y-axis of the grid.
1461
1462            :raises AssertionError: If unsuccessful in modifying the opacity in use by the Y-axis of the grid.
1463            :raises TimeoutException: If the Settings panel is not already displayed, or an axis is not already being
1464                edited.
1465            """
1466            self._grid_opacity.set_text(text=value)
1467            IAAssert.is_equal_to(
1468                actual_value=self._grid_opacity.wait_on_text_condition(
1469                    text_to_compare=value, condition=TextCondition.EQUALS),
1470                expected_value=value,
1471                as_type=str,
1472                failure_msg="Failed to set the opacity of the Y-axis of the grid while editing an axis.")
1473
1474        def set_grid_y_axis_dash_array(self, value: str) -> None:
1475            """
1476            Set the Y-axis dash-array to be used by the grid for the axis currently being edited.
1477
1478            :param value: The desired value to use for the dash-array of the Y-axis of the grid.
1479
1480            :raises AssertionError: If unsuccessful in modifying the dash-array in use by the Y-axis of the grid.
1481            :raises TimeoutException: If the Settings panel is not already displayed, or an axis is not already being
1482                edited.
1483            """
1484            self._grid_dash_array.set_text(text=value)
1485            IAAssert.is_equal_to(
1486                actual_value=self._grid_dash_array.wait_on_text_condition(
1487                    text_to_compare=value, condition=TextCondition.EQUALS),
1488                expected_value=value,
1489                as_type=str,
1490                failure_msg="Failed to set the dash-array of the Y-axis of the grid while editing an axis.")

1592        def click_pen_checkbox_by_name(self, pen_name: str) -> None:
1593            """
1594            Click the checkbox for a pen listed in the pen control table.
1595

1599            """
1600            self._pen_checkbox.set_locator(

1605        def click_pencil_icon_for_pen(self, pen_name: str) -> None:
1606            """
1607            Click the pencil icon for a pen in the pen control table.
1608
1609            :param pen_name: The name of the pen for which you would like to click the accompanying pencil icon.
1610
1611            :raises IndexError: If no pen with the supplied name could be found.
1612            """
1613            pen_label_web_element = list(
1614                filter(
1615                    lambda e: e.text == pen_name,
1616                    self._pen_labels.find_all(
1617                        wait_timeout=1)))[0]
1618            IASelenium(
1619                driver=self.driver).hover_over_web_element(
1620                web_element=pen_label_web_element)
1621            self._edit_pen_icon.set_locator(
1622                new_locator=(By.CSS_SELECTOR, "div.tr.hovering svg.edit-pen-icon"))
1623            self._edit_pen_icon.click()

1625        def get_all_pen_names_from_pen_table(self) -> List[str]:
1626            """
1627            Obtain the names of all pens displayed in the pen control table.
1628
1629            :returns: A list which contains the name of every pen displayed in the pen control table.
1630
1631            :raises TimeoutException: If the pen control table is not present.
1632            """
1633            row_count = self.get_count_of_rows()
1634            pen_names = []
1635            for i in range(row_count):
1636                pen_names.append(self.get_row_data_by_row_index(zero_based_row_index=i)['penName'])
1637            return pen_names

1639        def get_count_of_pen_fault_overlays(self) -> int:
1640            """
1641            Obtain a count of how many pens are currently displaying fault overlays.
1642
1643            :returns: A count of how many pens are currently displaying fault overlays.
1644            """
1645            try:
1646                return len(self._pen_overlay.find_all())
1647            except TimeoutException:
1648                return 0

1653            contains no header text.

1688        def pen_checkbox_is_active(self, pen_name: str) -> bool:
1689            """
1690            Determine if the checkbox of a pen is active (selected and/or checked are synonymous with active).
1691
1692            :param pen_name: The name of the pen for which we will check the accompanying checkbox.
1693
1694            :returns: True, if the checkbox for the specified pen is active/selected/checked.
1695
1696            :raises TimeoutException: If no pen with the supplied name is present in the pen control table, or if the
1697                pen control table is not present.
1698            """
1699            self._pen_checkbox.set_locator(
1700                new_locator=(
1701                    By.CSS_SELECTOR,
1702                    f'{self._UNFORMATTED_PEN_VISIBILITY_CHECKBOX_SELECTOR_STRING.format(pen_name)} > path'))
1703            return self._pen_checkbox.find().get_attribute('d') == self._PEN_CHECKBOX_SVG_CHECKED
1704
1705        def get_row_data_by_row_index(self, zero_based_row_index: int) -> dict:
1706            """
1707            Obtain the data of a specified row and return that data as a dictionary, where the keys of the dictionary
1708            are the column names.
1709
1710            :param zero_based_row_index: The zero-based index of the row you are targeting.
1711
1712            :returns: The row data as a dictionary, with the keys of the dictionary being the case-sensitive names of
1713                the columns.
1714            """
1715            row_data_as_dictionary = {}
1716            for cell in self._get_cell_components_by_row_index(zero_based_row_index=zero_based_row_index).find_all():
1717                row_data_as_dictionary[cell.get_attribute('data-column-id')] = cell.text
1718            row_data_as_dictionary.pop('toggle', None)
1719            return row_data_as_dictionary
1720
1721        def _get_cell_components_by_row_index(self, zero_based_row_index: int) -> ComponentPiece:
1722            """
1723            Obtain a ComponentPiece which describes how to locate the cells of a row of the pen control table.
1724
1725            :param zero_based_row_index: The zero-based index of the row these 'cells' would belong to.
1726            """
1727            cells = self._pen_control_table_cells_dict.get(zero_based_row_index)
1728            if not cells:
1729                cells = ComponentPiece(
1730                    locator=(By.CSS_SELECTOR, f'div.tr[data-row-index="{zero_based_row_index}"] div.tc'),
1731                    driver=self.driver,
1732                    parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
1733                    description=f"The cells from the {zero_based_row_index}th row in the pen control table.",
1734                    poll_freq=self.poll_freq)
1735                self._pen_control_table_cells_dict[zero_based_row_index] = cells
1736            return cells

1738        def pen_control_column_is_displayed(
1739                self, pen_control_column: Union[PenControlColumn, RangeBrushColumn]) -> bool:
1740            """
1741            Determine if a pen control column is displayed.
1742
1743            :param pen_control_column: The pen control column or range brush column to check for the presence of.
1744
1745            :returns: True, if the supplied column is displayed - False otherwise.
1746            """
1747            try:
1748                return self._get_pen_control_table_column(pen_control_column=pen_control_column).find(1) is not None
1749            except TimeoutException:
1750                return False
1751
1752        def _get_pen_control_table_column(
1753                self, pen_control_column: Union[PenControlColumn, RangeBrushColumn]):
1754            pen_control_column = pen_control_column.value
1755            _column = self._pen_control_columns.get(pen_control_column)
1756            if not _column:
1757                _column = ComponentPiece(
1758                    locator=(By.CSS_SELECTOR, f'div.thc[data-column-id="{pen_control_column}"]'),
1759                    driver=self.driver,
1760                    parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
1761                    description=f"The '{pen_control_column}' column from the pen control table of the Power Chart.",
1762                    poll_freq=self.poll_freq)
1763                self._pen_control_columns[pen_control_column] = _column
1764            return _column

1766        def pen_table_is_expanded(self) -> bool:
1767            """
1768            Determine if the pen control table is expanded.
1769
1770            :returns: True, if the pen control table is currently expanded - False otherwise.
1771            """
1772            try:
1773                return (self.find() is not None) \
1774                       and ("collapse-icon" in self._pen_table_expand_collapse_svg.find().get_attribute("class"))
1775            except TimeoutException:
1776                return False
1777
1778        def range_brush_column_is_displayed(self, range_brush_column: RangeBrushColumn) -> bool:
1779            """
1780            Determine if a range brush column is displayed in the pen control table.
1781
1782            :param range_brush_column: The range brush column for which we will check the display state.
1783
1784            :returns: True, if the supplied range brush column is displayed - False otherwise.
1785            """
1786            return self.pen_control_column_is_displayed(pen_control_column=range_brush_column)

1788        def remove_pen_by_name(self, pen_name: str) -> None:
1789            """
1790            Remove a pen from the pen control table (and therefore the Power Chart) via the pen control table.
1791
1792            :param pen_name: The name of the pen you would like to remove.
1793
1794            :raises AssertionError: If unsuccessful in removing the supplied pen from the Power Chart.
1795            :raises TimeoutException: If the pen control table is not present.
1796            """
1797            try:
1798                pen_label_web_element = list(filter(
1799                    lambda e: e.text == pen_name, self._pen_labels.find_all(wait_timeout=1)))[0]
1800                IASelenium(driver=self.driver).hover_over_web_element(web_element=pen_label_web_element)
1801                self._delete_pen_icon.set_locator(new_locator=(By.CSS_SELECTOR, "div.tr.hovering svg.delete-pen-icon"))
1802                self._delete_pen_icon.click()
1803                self._confirm_deletion_button.click()
1804            except IndexError:
1805                # no pen with name in controls
1806                pass
1807            IAAssert.does_not_contain(
1808                iterable=self.get_all_pen_names_from_pen_table(),
1809                expected_value=pen_name,
1810                failure_msg=f"The '{pen_name}' pen was still present in the pen control table after we attempted to "
1811                            f"remove it.")
1812
1813        def set_pen_visibility_on_pen_table(self, pen_name: str, should_be_visible: bool) -> None:
1814            """
1815            Set the display state (visibility) of a pen via the pen control table by interacting with the associated
1816            checkbox.
1817
1818            :param pen_name: The name of the pen which you would like to set the display state of.
1819            :param should_be_visible: If True, the checkbox will be set to active/selected/checked - otherwise the
1820                checkbox will be set to inactive/unselected/un-checked.
1821
1822            :raises AssertionError: If unsuccessful in setting the display state of the specified checkbox.
1823            :raises TimeoutException: if no pen with the supplied name is present, or if the pen control table is not
1824                present.
1825            """
1826            if self.pen_checkbox_is_active(pen_name=pen_name) != should_be_visible:
1827                self.click_pen_checkbox_by_name(pen_name=pen_name)
1828            IAAssert.is_equal_to(
1829                actual_value=self.pen_checkbox_is_active(pen_name=pen_name),
1830                expected_value=should_be_visible,
1831                failure_msg=f"Failed to set the display state (visibility) of the '{pen_name}' pen "
1832                            f"to {should_be_visible}.")
1833
1834        def toggle_pen_table_display(self) -> None:
1835            """
1836            Toggle the pen control table expansion state.
1837
1838            :raises TimeoutException: If the expand/collapse toggle icon is not present.
1839            """
1840            try:
1841                self._collapse_icon.click()
1842                self._expand_icon.find(wait_timeout=1)
1843            except TimeoutException:
1844                try:
1845                    self._expand_icon.click()
1846                    self._collapse_icon.find(wait_timeout=1)
1847                except TimeoutException as toe:
1848                    raise TimeoutException(
1849                        msg=f'Pen table collapse/expand icons could not be located for interaction.') from toe
1850
1851    class _PowerChartTagBrowser(CommonTagBrowseTree):
1852        """
1853        The Tag Browse Tree built into the Power Chart.
1854        """
1855        _ADD_TAG_BUTTON_LOCATOR = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, '.ia_button--primary')
1856        _CLOSE_ICON_LOCATOR = (By.ID, 'ia_powerChartComponent__tagBrowserContainer__closeIcon')
1857        _TAG_BROWSER_LOCATOR = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, 'div.ia_powerChartComponent__tagBrowserContainer')
1858        _TAG_BROWSER_OPEN_ICON_LOCATOR = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, 'span.show-tag-browser-icon')
1859        _RELOAD_ICON_LOCATOR = (By.ID, 'ia_powerChartComponent__tagBrowserContainer__reloadIcon')
1860
1861        def __init__(
1862                self,
1863                parent_locator_list: List[Tuple[By, str]],
1864                driver: WebDriver,
1865                poll_freq: float = 0.5):
1866            super().__init__(
1867                locator=self._TAG_BROWSER_LOCATOR,
1868                driver=driver,
1869                parent_locator_list=parent_locator_list,
1870                description="The Tag Browse Tree of the Power Chart.",
1871                poll_freq=poll_freq)
1872            self._add_tag_button = CommonButton(
1873                locator=self._ADD_TAG_BUTTON_LOCATOR,
1874                driver=driver,
1875                parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
1876                description="The 'Add Selected Tags' button at the bottom of the Tag Browse Tree.",
1877                poll_freq=poll_freq)
1878            self._close_icon = ComponentPiece(
1879                locator=self._CLOSE_ICON_LOCATOR,
1880                driver=driver,
1881                parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
1882                description="The arrow pointing left - and located in the upper-right of the Tag Browse Tree - which "
1883                            "collapses the Tag Browse Tree of the Power Chart.",
1884                poll_freq=poll_freq)
1885            self._reload_icon = ComponentPiece(
1886                locator=self._RELOAD_ICON_LOCATOR,
1887                driver=driver,
1888                parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
1889                description="The reload/refresh icon located in the upper-right of the Tag Browse Tree of the Power "
1890                            "Chart.",
1891                poll_freq=poll_freq)
1892
1893        def add_tags_to_chart(self, tag_paths: [str]) -> None:
1894            """
1895            Add tags to the Power Chart. Requires the Tag Browse Tree already be expanded. If all specified tags are
1896            already graphed, no action is taken, and the Tag Browse Tree will remain expanded.
1897
1898            :param tag_paths: A list of tag paths which describe the tags to add to the Power Chart graph as pens.
1899
1900            :raises TimeoutException: If any of the supplied paths does not map to a tag, or if the Tag Browse Tree is
1901                not present/expanded.
1902            """
1903            for tag_path in tag_paths:
1904                tag_name = self._split_item_label_path(tag_path)[-1]
1905                self._expand_tag_browser_tree_by_path(path=tag_path)
1906                try:
1907                    WebDriverWait(driver=self.driver, timeout=5).until(
1908                        IAec.function_returns_true(
1909                            custom_function=self._select_tag_to_be_added_later,
1910                            function_args={"tag_name": tag_name}))
1911                except TimeoutException as toe:
1912                    raise TimeoutException(msg=f"No tag found with a name of '{tag_name}'.") from toe
1913                # wait for Apply button to become enabled
1914                WebDriverWait(driver=self.driver, timeout=1).until(IAec.function_returns_true(
1915                    custom_function=self._add_tag_button.is_enabled, function_args={}))
1916                if self._add_tag_button.is_enabled():
1917                    # tag might already be displayed in the chart, so we might not need to add it
1918                    self._add_tag_button.click(binding_wait_time=1)
1919
1920        def click_reload_icon(self) -> None:
1921            """
1922            Click the reload icon of the Tag Browse Tree.
1923
1924            :raises TimeoutException: If the Tag Browse Tree is not expanded in the Power Chart.
1925            """
1926            self._reload_icon.click(binding_wait_time=1)
1927
1928        def collapse_if_expanded(self) -> None:
1929            """
1930            Collapse the Tag Browse Tree if it is currently expanded. If the Tag Browse Tree is already collapsed, then
1931            no action is taken.
1932            """
1933            if self.tag_browser_is_expanded():
1934                self._close_icon.click()
1935
1936        def is_displayed(self) -> bool:
1937            """
1938            Determine if the Tag Browse Tree is displayed.
1939
1940            :returns: True, if the Tag Browse Tree is currently displayed - False otherwise.
1941            """
1942            return self.tag_browser_is_expanded()
1943
1944        def is_in_responsive_mode(self) -> bool:
1945            """
1946            Determine if the Tag Browse Tree is in responsive mode.
1947
1948            :returns: True, if the Tag Browse Tree is currently rendering in responsive mode.
1949            """
1950            return "mobile" in self.find().get_attribute(name="class")
1951
1952        def tag_browser_is_expanded(self) -> bool:
1953            """
1954            Determine if the Tag Browse Tree is expanded.
1955
1956            :returns: True, if the tag Browse Tree is currently expanded - False otherwise.
1957            """
1958            try:
1959                return 'expanded' in self.find(wait_timeout=1).get_attribute('class')
1960            except TimeoutException:
1961                return False
1962
1963        def _expand_tag_browser_tree_by_path(self, path: str) -> None:
1964            """
1965            Expand the Tag Browse Tree structure based on a supplied tag path.
1966
1967            :param path: The path of a Tag as a slash-delimited string.
1968            """
1969            path_nodes = self._split_item_label_path(path)
1970            for i in path_nodes:
1971                try:
1972                    if self.item_label_exists_in_tree(item_label=i) and \
1973                            not self.item_is_expanded(item_label=i) \
1974                            and (path_nodes.index(i) != len(path_nodes)-1):
1975                        folder_index = self._get_index_of_item_in_tree(item_label=i)
1976                        self._folder_icons.find_all()[folder_index].click()
1977                        self.wait_on_binding(time_to_wait=1)
1978                        WebDriverWait(driver=self.driver, timeout=3, poll_frequency=self.poll_freq).until(
1979                            IAec.function_returns_true(
1980                                custom_function=self.item_is_expanded,
1981                                function_args={'item_label': i}))
1982                except TimeoutException as toe:
1983                    raise TimeoutException(
1984                        msg=f"Tag browser tree might not have expanded as expected.\nCheck that the provided "
1985                            f"path \'{path}\' is correct.") from toe
1986
1987        def _select_tag_to_be_added_later(self, tag_name: str) -> bool:
1988            """
1989            Select a singular tag for later addition to the Power Chart.
1990
1991            :param tag_name: The name of the tag to select now, for later addition to the Power Chart graph.
1992
1993            :returns: True, if the supplied tag name was selected successfully - False otherwise.
1994            """
1995            try:
1996                self.click_item_label(item_label=tag_name)
1997                return True
1998            except TimeoutException:
1999                return False
2000
2001    def __init__(
2002            self,
2003            locator: Tuple[By, str],
2004            driver: WebDriver,
2005            parent_locator_list: Optional[List[Tuple[By, str]]] = None,
2006            wait_timeout: float = 10,
2007            description: Optional[str] = None,
2008            poll_freq: float = 0.5):
2009        super().__init__(
2010            locator=locator,
2011            driver=driver,
2012            parent_locator_list=parent_locator_list,
2013            wait_timeout=wait_timeout,
2014            description=description,
2015            poll_freq=poll_freq)
2016        self._footer = self._PowerChartFooter(
2017            parent_locator_list=self.locator_list, driver=driver, poll_freq=poll_freq)
2018        self._graph = self._PowerChartGraph(
2019            parent_locator_list=self.locator_list, driver=driver, poll_freq=poll_freq)
2020        self._header = self._PowerChartHeader(
2021            parent_locator_list=self.locator_list, driver=driver, poll_freq=poll_freq)
2022        self._pen_control_table = self._PowerChartTable(
2023            parent_locator_list=self.locator_list, driver=driver, poll_freq=poll_freq)
2024        self._settings_panel = self._PowerChartSettingsPanel(
2025            parent_locator_list=self.locator_list, driver=driver, poll_freq=poll_freq)
2026        self._tag_browser = self._PowerChartTagBrowser(
2027            parent_locator_list=self.locator_list, driver=driver, poll_freq=poll_freq)

2029    def add_tags_to_chart(self, tag_paths: [str]) -> None:
2030        """
2031        Add tags to the chart to be graphed as pens. This function will expand the Tag Browser if it is not already
2032        expanded, and will leave the Tag Browser expansion state as it was before this function was invoked.
2033
2034        :param tag_paths: A list containing the full tag paths of each tag to add.
2035
2036        :raises TimeoutException: If the Tag Browser button is not present, or if any supplied tag path does not
2037            identify a Tag to be added.
2038        """
2039        _original_state = self._tag_browser.tag_browser_is_expanded()
2040        if not _original_state:
2041            self._header.click_tag_browser_button()
2042        self._tag_browser.add_tags_to_chart(tag_paths=tag_paths)
2043        self.wait_on_binding(time_to_wait=2)  # wait for tags to be graphed
2044        if not _original_state:
2045            self._tag_browser.collapse_if_expanded()
2046

2356    def get_graph_path(self, pen_name: str) -> str:
2357        """
2358        Obtain the drawn path of a graphed pen. Useful for determining when a graphed pen has updated.
2359
2360        :param pen_name: The name of the pen for which you would like the path of the graphed line.
2361
2362        :returns: A string which represents the actual graphed line of a pen.
2363
2364        :raises IndexError: If unable to link the supplied pen name to a graphed line by the color of the pen's
2365            checkbox.
2366        :raises TimeoutException: If no pen with the supplied name is present in the pen control table, or if no pens
2367            are graphed at all.
2368        """
2369        return self._graph.get_drawn_path(pen_checkbox_color_as_string=self.get_pen_checkbox_color(pen_name=pen_name))

2627    def select_historical_range(self, historical_range: HistoricalRange) -> None:
2628        """
2629        Apply the values of a HistoricalRange object to the Power Chart. This convenience function handles expansion,
2630        application, and confirmation of the supplied values.
2631
2632        :param historical_range: A HistoricalRange object which contains all of the information about the range to be
2633            selected.
2634
2635        :raises AssertionError: If unsuccessful in applying the provided range.
2636        """
2637        self._header.open_date_range_selector_if_not_displayed()
2638        self._header.select_date_range_selector_tab(tab=DateRangeSelectorTab.HISTORICAL)
2639        self._header.set_historical_month(month=historical_range.beginning_month)
2640        self._header.set_historical_year(year=historical_range.beginning_year)
2641        self._header.set_historical_day(numeric_day=historical_range.beginning_day)
2642        self._header.set_historical_month(month=historical_range.ending_month)
2643        self._header.set_historical_year(year=historical_range.ending_year)
2644        self._header.set_historical_day(numeric_day=historical_range.ending_day)
2645        self._header.apply_changes()
2646
2647    def select_realtime_range(self, time_value: int, time_unit: DateRangeSelectorTimeUnit) -> None:
2648        """
2649        Select the scalar value of time and the time unit to use for the realtime range of the Power Chart.
2650
2651        :param time_value: The scalar amount of time to apply.
2652        :param time_unit: The unit of time to apply.
2653
2654        :raises TimeoutException: If the range selector is not present.
2655        """
2656        self._header.open_date_range_selector_if_not_displayed()
2657        self._header.select_date_range_selector_tab(tab=DateRangeSelectorTab.REALTIME)
2658        self._header.set_realtime_numeric_value(time_value=time_value)
2659        self._header.select_realtime_unit(time_unit=time_unit)
2660        self._header.apply_changes()

2008            poll_freq: float = 0.5):
2009        super().__init__(
2010            locator=locator,
2011            driver=driver,
2012            parent_locator_list=parent_locator_list,
2013            wait_timeout=wait_timeout,
2014            description=description,
2015            poll_freq=poll_freq)
2016        self._footer = self._PowerChartFooter(
2017            parent_locator_list=self.locator_list, driver=driver, poll_freq=poll_freq)
2018        self._graph = self._PowerChartGraph(
2019            parent_locator_list=self.locator_list, driver=driver, poll_freq=poll_freq)
2020        self._header = self._PowerChartHeader(
2021            parent_locator_list=self.locator_list, driver=driver, poll_freq=poll_freq)
2022        self._pen_control_table = self._PowerChartTable(
2023            parent_locator_list=self.locator_list, driver=driver, poll_freq=poll_freq)
2024        self._settings_panel = self._PowerChartSettingsPanel(
2025            parent_locator_list=self.locator_list, driver=driver, poll_freq=poll_freq)
2026        self._tag_browser = self._PowerChartTagBrowser(
2027            parent_locator_list=self.locator_list, driver=driver, poll_freq=poll_freq)

locator: Tuple A tuple which defines the CSS selector which would be used to locate the component. driver: WebDriver The WebDriver used to drive the session/page. parent_locator_list: List A list of the locators used to build the parent of this component. A value of None will be interpreted as opting into ignorance of the parentage of the component. wait_timeout: float The amount of time to poll the DOM before throwing a potential TimeoutException in the event this component could not be located. poll_freq: float A value used to determine how frequently to poll the DOM. Used primarily for performance testing.

2361

2365            checkbox.
2366        :raises TimeoutException: If no pen with the supplied name is present in the pen control table, or if no pens
2367            are graphed at all.
2368        """
2369        return self._graph.get_drawn_path(pen_checkbox_color_as_string=self.get_pen_checkbox_color(pen_name=pen_name))

2628        """
2629        Apply the values of a HistoricalRange object to the Power Chart. This convenience function handles expansion,
2630        application, and confirmation of the supplied values.

2641        self._header.set_historical_day(numeric_day=historical_range.beginning_day)
2642        self._header.set_historical_month(month=historical_range.ending_month)
2643        self._header.set_historical_year(year=historical_range.ending_year)
2644        self._header.set_historical_day(numeric_day=historical_range.ending_day)
